WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.035 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.035 --> 00:00:06.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH:
Most of us can

00:00:06.410 --> 00:00:09.590 align:middle line:84%
feel the pain of the crumbling
old structures around us.

00:00:09.590 --> 00:00:11.560 align:middle line:10%
The anxiety often
comes in not knowing

00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:15.180 align:middle line:10%
what the future holds for our
children and grandchildren.

00:00:15.180 --> 00:00:17.520 align:middle line:84%
Author Kingsley Dennis
says that their future

00:00:17.520 --> 00:00:20.410 align:middle line:84%
is going to be more innovative,
creative, and whole.

00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:24.354 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:24.354 --> 00:00:44.567 align:middle line:90%


00:00:44.567 --> 00:00:47.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Dennis thank you from
flying all the way to Spain

00:00:47.160 --> 00:00:50.150 align:middle line:84%
to our little studio
here in London.

00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:51.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm really intrigued
with your work,

00:00:51.730 --> 00:00:54.720 align:middle line:84%
because I look at what we have
left the next generations,

00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:57.760 align:middle line:84%
which isn't much-- not
economically, socially,

00:00:57.760 --> 00:00:58.710 align:middle line:90%
or otherwise.

00:00:58.710 --> 00:01:00.510 align:middle line:84%
And you're talking
about the fact

00:01:00.510 --> 00:01:02.730 align:middle line:84%
that it doesn't
matter, because these

00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:06.440 align:middle line:84%
are an entirely different
kind of beings, so to speak,

00:01:06.440 --> 00:01:08.900 align:middle line:84%
that are going to create the
world in a new way, called

00:01:08.900 --> 00:01:10.000 align:middle line:90%
the phoenix generation.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:12.419 align:middle line:84%
And so before we get into
what the phoenix generation is

00:01:12.419 --> 00:01:13.960 align:middle line:84%
and what you expect
from them, do you

00:01:13.960 --> 00:01:15.730 align:middle line:90%
mind if I read from your book?

00:01:15.730 --> 00:01:19.050 align:middle line:84%
It was right up front, a
quote from Buckminster Fuller.

00:01:19.050 --> 00:01:21.380 align:middle line:84%
It says, "Traditional
human power structures

00:01:21.380 --> 00:01:26.270 align:middle line:84%
and their reign of darkness are
about to be rendered obsolete,

00:01:26.270 --> 00:01:28.630 align:middle line:84%
not taken asunder, but
rendered obsolete."

00:01:28.630 --> 00:01:30.320 align:middle line:84%
So explain why you
put that up front.

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:32.540 align:middle line:84%
>>KINGSLEY DENNIS:
Oh, thank you, Regina.

00:01:32.540 --> 00:01:35.930 align:middle line:10%
Buckminster Fuller was a
visionary in his own right,

00:01:35.930 --> 00:01:41.850 align:middle line:10%
and he was-- he knew very
well how things change,

00:01:41.850 --> 00:01:43.350 align:middle line:10%
how systems change.

00:01:43.350 --> 00:01:45.840 align:middle line:10%
And that is not necessarily
a case of things

00:01:45.840 --> 00:01:47.940 align:middle line:10%
happening overnight.

00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:50.690 align:middle line:84%
But how do we bring
in the new models?

00:01:50.690 --> 00:01:53.670 align:middle line:84%
And he knew, way back
then, many decades before,

00:01:53.670 --> 00:01:57.050 align:middle line:84%
that we're dealing with
incumbent systems that

00:01:57.050 --> 00:02:01.015 align:middle line:84%
are obsolete, and they've
passed their due date.

00:02:01.015 --> 00:02:04.200 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like to also
refer to another quote

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:06.200 align:middle line:84%
from Buckminster
Fuller, which I also

00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:08.110 align:middle line:90%
think hits the nail on the head.

00:02:08.110 --> 00:02:12.920 align:middle line:84%
And he said that, "we don't
fight the existing reality.

00:02:12.920 --> 00:02:14.970 align:middle line:84%
We need to create
new models that

00:02:14.970 --> 00:02:17.900 align:middle line:84%
make the existing
reality obsolete."

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And what he's
referring to is how

00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:23.960 align:middle line:84%
we need to respond
to incumbent systems

00:02:23.960 --> 00:02:28.590 align:middle line:84%
and that often the first wave,
the first reaction or response,

00:02:28.590 --> 00:02:32.080 align:middle line:84%
which is very human, when we
see the inequality in the world,

00:02:32.080 --> 00:02:35.290 align:middle line:84%
is that we wish to fight
against it directly.

00:02:35.290 --> 00:02:38.200 align:middle line:84%
We wish to protest,
which we often see now,

00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:41.470 align:middle line:84%
in the first wave
reactions around the world.

00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:45.020 align:middle line:84%
Well, this other approach,
the other response,

00:02:45.020 --> 00:02:48.870 align:middle line:84%
which is coming in over time,
is that rather than protest

00:02:48.870 --> 00:02:52.830 align:middle line:84%
head on, which only really
strengthens incumbent systems

00:02:52.830 --> 00:02:55.317 align:middle line:84%
and gives the
present status quo.

00:02:55.317 --> 00:02:57.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Everyone entrenches
into their position.

00:02:57.400 --> 00:02:58.025 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yeah.

00:02:58.025 --> 00:02:59.940 align:middle line:84%
And it gives them
more power to look

00:02:59.940 --> 00:03:03.060 align:middle line:84%
at what we're dealing
with, back into propaganda.

00:03:03.060 --> 00:03:04.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, exactly.

00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:07.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: So what Buckminster
Fuller is referring to--

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:10.420 align:middle line:84%
and I quote also in the
book-- is how we need

00:03:10.420 --> 00:03:12.720 align:middle line:84%
and how the phoenix
generation, we're

00:03:12.720 --> 00:03:16.720 align:middle line:84%
part of that incoming wave
that will be more savvy, more

00:03:16.720 --> 00:03:20.220 align:middle line:84%
instinctual, and will have an
understanding that in order

00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:23.310 align:middle line:84%
to make real change,
long-term change,

00:03:23.310 --> 00:03:26.360 align:middle line:84%
it's about bypassing
the incumbent systems

00:03:26.360 --> 00:03:29.180 align:middle line:84%
and creating new models
that eventually will just

00:03:29.180 --> 00:03:31.110 align:middle line:90%
outgrow and overtake.

00:03:31.110 --> 00:03:33.412 align:middle line:84%
They will replace
the existing systems.

00:03:33.412 --> 00:03:35.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that
makes perfect sense.

00:03:35.120 --> 00:03:36.840 align:middle line:84%
And that's how nature
works, isn't it?

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And everything human
beings have been doing

00:03:38.900 --> 00:03:41.250 align:middle line:84%
is going against nature,
thinking we can somehow

00:03:41.250 --> 00:03:43.806 align:middle line:84%
go against natural
principles and have it work.

00:03:43.806 --> 00:03:44.430 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't.

00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:49.570 align:middle line:84%
As you say, it just reinforces
already obsolete and not

00:03:49.570 --> 00:03:52.180 align:middle line:84%
particularly healthy
systems, right?

00:03:52.180 --> 00:03:54.540 align:middle line:84%
So now we can go
into-- and we will

00:03:54.540 --> 00:03:57.450 align:middle line:84%
have a few airplanes flying
overhead, because all of London

00:03:57.450 --> 00:03:59.650 align:middle line:84%
is in the Heathrow
flight path, right?

00:03:59.650 --> 00:04:02.260 align:middle line:84%
So we'll hear little bit of
that shadow in the background.

00:04:02.260 --> 00:04:06.280 align:middle line:84%
But let's talk about
phoenix generation itself,

00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:09.410 align:middle line:84%
the years we're talking about,
when these people were born,

00:04:09.410 --> 00:04:14.140 align:middle line:84%
when they will be coming
of age and into power.

00:04:14.140 --> 00:04:18.519 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: When I name
the phoenix generation,

00:04:18.519 --> 00:04:21.899 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking about a generation
that are being born around now,

00:04:21.899 --> 00:04:24.290 align:middle line:84%
in the years now,
a few years before,

00:04:24.290 --> 00:04:27.620 align:middle line:84%
but will come of
age around 2030.

00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:30.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So kind
of 2010 onward.

00:04:30.090 --> 00:04:31.150 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yeah.

00:04:31.150 --> 00:04:34.300 align:middle line:84%
And also because
around 2030, they

00:04:34.300 --> 00:04:37.880 align:middle line:84%
will be coming of age in a way
that they will be entering--

00:04:37.880 --> 00:04:41.686 align:middle line:84%
entering the workforce,
entering systems--

00:04:41.686 --> 00:04:46.320 align:middle line:84%
and will have a greater capacity
to engage with those systems.

00:04:46.320 --> 00:04:48.540 align:middle line:90%
So we're dealing with them now.

00:04:48.540 --> 00:04:53.120 align:middle line:84%
But of course, they're also a
part of a second or third wave,

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:56.490 align:middle line:84%
because they've been
coming in for a while,

00:04:56.490 --> 00:04:58.941 align:middle line:90%
but in very-- in lower numbers.

00:04:58.941 --> 00:05:01.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What about the
generation right before them,

00:05:01.190 --> 00:05:07.130 align:middle line:84%
the ones that started coming
in, say, around late '90s, 2000?

00:05:07.130 --> 00:05:08.680 align:middle line:84%
Because they're
kind of interesting.

00:05:08.680 --> 00:05:12.050 align:middle line:84%
I mean, each wave
is sort of built

00:05:12.050 --> 00:05:14.800 align:middle line:84%
upon the one before, right,
in laying the foundation.

00:05:14.800 --> 00:05:19.120 align:middle line:84%
What is the one that is around
18 years of age right now?

00:05:19.120 --> 00:05:21.650 align:middle line:84%
What have they laid,
by way of a foundation,

00:05:21.650 --> 00:05:24.050 align:middle line:84%
for this incoming
phoenix generation?

00:05:24.050 --> 00:05:25.630 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Well,
the earlier wave,

00:05:25.630 --> 00:05:28.320 align:middle line:84%
they often-- I feel
that, in fact, they've

00:05:28.320 --> 00:05:31.830 align:middle line:84%
had a harder time,
because of one way

00:05:31.830 --> 00:05:33.500 align:middle line:84%
is that they've come
into a system which

00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:36.350 align:middle line:84%
is more difficult,
more intangible

00:05:36.350 --> 00:05:38.000 align:middle line:90%
for them to deal with.

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:40.740 align:middle line:84%
And also, I feel part
of the responsibility

00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:44.370 align:middle line:84%
is from our side, because
we've stigmatized them.

00:05:44.370 --> 00:05:47.020 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by that
is, some of the earlier

00:05:47.020 --> 00:05:49.600 align:middle line:84%
references to them, we're
familiar with-- the indigo

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:51.590 align:middle line:90%
children, for example.

00:05:51.590 --> 00:05:54.122 align:middle line:84%
And they've been named crystal
children, star children.

00:05:54.122 --> 00:05:56.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're talking
about the phoenix generation

00:05:56.330 --> 00:05:57.635 align:middle line:90%
right now, or the one before?

00:05:57.635 --> 00:05:58.510 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: One before.

00:05:58.510 --> 00:05:59.509 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, all right.

00:05:59.509 --> 00:06:00.115 align:middle line:90%
Gotcha.

00:06:00.115 --> 00:06:02.630 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: So the
earlier wave-- and there

00:06:02.630 --> 00:06:06.430 align:middle line:84%
was a lot of news about
calling them indigo children.

00:06:06.430 --> 00:06:09.360 align:middle line:84%
And there were
comment about they

00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:12.010 align:middle line:84%
had maybe super-psychic
abilities.

00:06:12.010 --> 00:06:15.630 align:middle line:84%
And I think we went off in
slightly a different direction.

00:06:15.630 --> 00:06:19.930 align:middle line:84%
Now, going back to the--
that earlier stage.

00:06:19.930 --> 00:06:22.970 align:middle line:84%
Now, the indigo, the
origin of the indigo

00:06:22.970 --> 00:06:28.070 align:middle line:84%
is because-- I think it
refers to Nancy Ann Tappe, who

00:06:28.070 --> 00:06:31.950 align:middle line:84%
had a neurological condition
called synesthesia,

00:06:31.950 --> 00:06:35.950 align:middle line:90%
where she saw people as colors.

00:06:35.950 --> 00:06:39.120 align:middle line:84%
And so she saw people's
behavior and attitude as colors.

00:06:39.120 --> 00:06:41.710 align:middle line:84%
And so that under-- people's
behaviors and attitudes

00:06:41.710 --> 00:06:43.250 align:middle line:90%
came across.

00:06:43.250 --> 00:06:46.190 align:middle line:84%
And she saw the new color
coming in as indigo,

00:06:46.190 --> 00:06:49.160 align:middle line:84%
more children come in
with that behavior.

00:06:49.160 --> 00:06:52.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, it didn't suggest that
they were super-psychic.

00:06:52.050 --> 00:06:54.380 align:middle line:84%
It's just they did
things differently.

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:56.915 align:middle line:84%
They were having
different perspectives.

00:06:56.915 --> 00:07:00.570 align:middle line:84%
Now, I feel that we did a
slight disservice to them

00:07:00.570 --> 00:07:02.460 align:middle line:90%
by over-stigmatizing them.

00:07:02.460 --> 00:07:03.440 align:middle line:90%
They are indigo.

00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:05.900 align:middle line:84%
They're going to change
the world suddenly.

00:07:05.900 --> 00:07:08.580 align:middle line:84%
And yet, we saw instances
where they really

00:07:08.580 --> 00:07:11.590 align:middle line:84%
just-- a lot of them
hit, slapped face-on

00:07:11.590 --> 00:07:12.570 align:middle line:90%
with the systems.

00:07:12.570 --> 00:07:16.040 align:middle line:90%
They had difficulties.

00:07:16.040 --> 00:07:19.547 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, there was a huge
spurt in autism at that time,

00:07:19.547 --> 00:07:20.630 align:middle line:90%
too, certainly in America.

00:07:20.630 --> 00:07:22.746 align:middle line:90%
I don't know about Britain.

00:07:22.746 --> 00:07:24.440 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: True.

00:07:24.440 --> 00:07:26.490 align:middle line:84%
And I think the terminology
and understanding

00:07:26.490 --> 00:07:28.160 align:middle line:90%
got slightly mixed.

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:31.000 align:middle line:84%
My feeling is that
those known as indigo

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:33.600 align:middle line:84%
were just an earlier wave
of young children being

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:35.474 align:middle line:90%
born with different wiring.

00:07:35.474 --> 00:07:37.640 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're talking
about with the phoenix

00:07:37.640 --> 00:07:38.740 align:middle line:90%
generation.

00:07:38.740 --> 00:07:40.830 align:middle line:84%
It's that they're coming
with a different wiring.

00:07:40.830 --> 00:07:42.038 align:middle line:90%
They're thinking differently.

00:07:42.038 --> 00:07:44.390 align:middle line:84%
They understand
concepts differently.

00:07:44.390 --> 00:07:46.690 align:middle line:84%
And importantly,
they're shifting

00:07:46.690 --> 00:07:50.870 align:middle line:84%
from relying on
acquired information.

00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:52.000 align:middle line:90%
Now acquired information--

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:55.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're going to go
deeply into that, because, yes.

00:07:55.780 --> 00:07:59.060 align:middle line:84%
They were born into the matrix
as it's been shifting already,

00:07:59.060 --> 00:08:02.820 align:middle line:84%
and so it's been laid
for them, both on kind

00:08:02.820 --> 00:08:05.090 align:middle line:84%
of a programmed
level, energetically,

00:08:05.090 --> 00:08:08.495 align:middle line:84%
and in terms of data, what
they can have access to.

00:08:08.495 --> 00:08:10.090 align:middle line:90%
I find that really fascinating.

00:08:10.090 --> 00:08:13.070 align:middle line:84%
But you say that they're--
it's not going to be the end

00:08:13.070 --> 00:08:13.630 align:middle line:90%
of things.

00:08:13.630 --> 00:08:16.990 align:middle line:84%
We've all-- the other
past generations

00:08:16.990 --> 00:08:20.150 align:middle line:84%
have all been looking for the
end of a way, the end of this,

00:08:20.150 --> 00:08:21.264 align:middle line:90%
the end of times.

00:08:21.264 --> 00:08:22.680 align:middle line:84%
You're saying it's
not about that.

00:08:22.680 --> 00:08:24.550 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: No, I don't
think there is an end.

00:08:24.550 --> 00:08:28.210 align:middle line:84%
I think, really, we've been
focusing too much on the end.

00:08:28.210 --> 00:08:30.470 align:middle line:84%
And we can talk all day
about 2012 and where

00:08:30.470 --> 00:08:33.564 align:middle line:84%
that kind of grew
and that phenomenon.

00:08:33.564 --> 00:08:37.179 align:middle line:84%
But really, there's been too
much talk about end times

00:08:37.179 --> 00:08:38.360 align:middle line:90%
or the end of this.

00:08:38.360 --> 00:08:42.520 align:middle line:84%
Really, if we look at the whole
history of human civilization

00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:45.980 align:middle line:84%
and the whole growth
of human consciousness,

00:08:45.980 --> 00:08:48.250 align:middle line:84%
it's about evolving
systems, in terms

00:08:48.250 --> 00:08:52.600 align:middle line:84%
of civilization and ongoing
evolving consciousness.

00:08:52.600 --> 00:08:53.870 align:middle line:90%
There has been no end.

00:08:53.870 --> 00:08:56.190 align:middle line:84%
There's just been
different phases.

00:08:56.190 --> 00:09:00.320 align:middle line:84%
So we can see
transition moments.

00:09:00.320 --> 00:09:01.910 align:middle line:84%
And within that
transition moment,

00:09:01.910 --> 00:09:07.430 align:middle line:84%
we can see there has been end
of some patterns of thinking.

00:09:07.430 --> 00:09:08.060 align:middle line:90%
We can go back.

00:09:08.060 --> 00:09:11.220 align:middle line:84%
There's a classic one we say
now-- the leap from the world

00:09:11.220 --> 00:09:13.676 align:middle line:90%
was flat to the world was round.

00:09:13.676 --> 00:09:15.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
that's what you say

00:09:15.050 --> 00:09:16.960 align:middle line:84%
the phoenix
generation brings in,

00:09:16.960 --> 00:09:19.890 align:middle line:84%
that degree of shift in
consciousness and awareness.

00:09:19.890 --> 00:09:21.730 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: I do feel
that we'll look back

00:09:21.730 --> 00:09:24.990 align:middle line:84%
on this time as being as
significant as shifting

00:09:24.990 --> 00:09:27.120 align:middle line:84%
from a flat earth
to a round earth.

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:29.580 align:middle line:84%
Because when we have
that shift, it's

00:09:29.580 --> 00:09:32.880 align:middle line:84%
a shift in perspectives,
a shift in perception,

00:09:32.880 --> 00:09:35.920 align:middle line:84%
a shift in the capacity
of consciousness

00:09:35.920 --> 00:09:39.370 align:middle line:84%
to affect our social
systems and civilization.

00:09:39.370 --> 00:09:41.490 align:middle line:90%
They're convergent points.

00:09:41.490 --> 00:09:45.300 align:middle line:84%
So we have smaller
transitions, smaller movements.

00:09:45.300 --> 00:09:47.550 align:middle line:84%
And then there's
times in human history

00:09:47.550 --> 00:09:49.760 align:middle line:90%
when everything converges.

00:09:49.760 --> 00:09:51.855 align:middle line:84%
And that makes it
a grander moment.

00:09:51.855 --> 00:09:55.035 align:middle line:84%
And that, I feel, is what's
coming in now at the same time

00:09:55.035 --> 00:09:57.050 align:middle line:84%
frame, a generational
time frame,

00:09:57.050 --> 00:09:58.430 align:middle line:90%
as the phoenix generation.

00:09:58.430 --> 00:09:59.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:09:59.140 --> 00:10:01.750 align:middle line:84%
If we can divert for just a
moment, because I was intrigued

00:10:01.750 --> 00:10:05.339 align:middle line:84%
a moment ago when you said, I
can go on about the 2012 thing.

00:10:05.339 --> 00:10:07.380 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you gone on a
bit about the 2012 thing?

00:10:07.380 --> 00:10:09.588 align:middle line:84%
Then we'll pick it back up
with the phoenix children.

00:10:09.588 --> 00:10:13.690 align:middle line:84%
And we need to look
at these-- I don't

00:10:13.690 --> 00:10:17.220 align:middle line:84%
know if you call it an agenda,
that have been laid out for us,

00:10:17.220 --> 00:10:20.350 align:middle line:84%
where everyone essentially
goes into fear mode and fear

00:10:20.350 --> 00:10:23.420 align:middle line:84%
patterns, which is what
happened over 2012.

00:10:23.420 --> 00:10:24.855 align:middle line:90%
Tell us your take on 2012.

00:10:24.855 --> 00:10:27.580 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Well, I think
it's fairly obvious now,

00:10:27.580 --> 00:10:32.120 align:middle line:84%
when we look back on it, that it
was-- the information was also

00:10:32.120 --> 00:10:33.900 align:middle line:90%
hijacked, as well.

00:10:33.900 --> 00:10:36.320 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the
information was manipulated

00:10:36.320 --> 00:10:40.100 align:middle line:84%
to turn this-- initially
this understanding

00:10:40.100 --> 00:10:43.830 align:middle line:84%
that it's a moment of great
change into a new cycle

00:10:43.830 --> 00:10:45.471 align:middle line:84%
into something
that's the end times.

00:10:45.471 --> 00:10:47.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Somehow, it became
mixed up with apocalyptic news.

00:10:47.970 --> 00:10:48.435 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yeah.

00:10:48.435 --> 00:10:48.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:10:48.900 --> 00:10:50.610 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: We've always
had those moments.

00:10:50.610 --> 00:10:52.980 align:middle line:84%
We had a smaller moment
in the Millennium bug,

00:10:52.980 --> 00:10:56.080 align:middle line:84%
when it was changing to, oh,
dear, we've reached 2000.

00:10:56.080 --> 00:10:59.960 align:middle line:84%
All the planes are going
to drop out of the sky.

00:10:59.960 --> 00:11:02.900 align:middle line:90%
Fear is a great propaganda tool.

00:11:02.900 --> 00:11:06.200 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, fear really
is the main energy

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:08.930 align:middle line:90%
of mainstream traditional news.

00:11:08.930 --> 00:11:09.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:11:09.890 --> 00:11:11.723 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: I mean, if
you look at propaganda,

00:11:11.723 --> 00:11:13.890 align:middle line:84%
the history of propaganda,
which was set up--

00:11:13.890 --> 00:11:16.830 align:middle line:84%
one of the godfathers of
propaganda was Edward Bernays.

00:11:16.830 --> 00:11:19.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yes.

00:11:19.370 --> 00:11:22.500 align:middle line:84%
There's a wonderful documentary
called, "The Century of Self."

00:11:22.500 --> 00:11:24.350 align:middle line:84%
So anyone who hasn't
seen that, I highly

00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:26.370 align:middle line:84%
recommend them watching
"The Century of Self,"

00:11:26.370 --> 00:11:29.450 align:middle line:84%
very revealing, to see
just how manipulated

00:11:29.450 --> 00:11:31.160 align:middle line:90%
the fabric of society has been.

00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:34.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And that
matrix of misinformation,

00:11:34.240 --> 00:11:36.430 align:middle line:90%
it absorbed 2012.

00:11:36.430 --> 00:11:41.980 align:middle line:84%
And so one of the factors of
2012 which were against us

00:11:41.980 --> 00:11:45.850 align:middle line:84%
was it put people in limbo,
in that we didn't quite

00:11:45.850 --> 00:11:47.970 align:middle line:84%
know what was going
to happen post-2012.

00:11:47.970 --> 00:11:50.710 align:middle line:84%
Were we going to
ascend somewhere?

00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:53.250 align:middle line:84%
Or were we going to just
completely evaporate?

00:11:53.250 --> 00:11:56.114 align:middle line:84%
So people were
waiting, and waiting

00:11:56.114 --> 00:11:57.780 align:middle line:84%
to really understand
what was happening.

00:11:57.780 --> 00:12:02.730 align:middle line:84%
And I think that took away
some of our activity, in that I

00:12:02.730 --> 00:12:05.160 align:middle line:84%
think there's been a
greater energetic spurt

00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:07.930 align:middle line:84%
of creative projects
and new thinking

00:12:07.930 --> 00:12:10.595 align:middle line:84%
post 2012 because people
have realized that--

00:12:10.595 --> 00:12:12.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It was on pause, yes.

00:12:12.820 --> 00:12:15.950 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't just a
new age projection;

00:12:15.950 --> 00:12:19.080 align:middle line:84%
it was lining up with
fundamentalist Christianity,

00:12:19.080 --> 00:12:22.130 align:middle line:84%
for example, where a lot of
these stories and looking

00:12:22.130 --> 00:12:25.180 align:middle line:84%
for the signs at the end were
starting to align together.

00:12:25.180 --> 00:12:28.510 align:middle line:84%
So you had, really,
a large percentage

00:12:28.510 --> 00:12:31.010 align:middle line:84%
of the population--
if you then expand it

00:12:31.010 --> 00:12:33.740 align:middle line:84%
to that population--
expecting some kind of end.

00:12:33.740 --> 00:12:35.120 align:middle line:90%
Well, life is on pause.

00:12:35.120 --> 00:12:37.370 align:middle line:84%
You're not really striving
for anything at that point,

00:12:37.370 --> 00:12:38.190 align:middle line:90%
like you said.

00:12:38.190 --> 00:12:40.660 align:middle line:84%
And these children were
being born during that time.

00:12:40.660 --> 00:12:41.410 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Exactly.

00:12:41.410 --> 00:12:43.360 align:middle line:84%
And what type of--
those messages

00:12:43.360 --> 00:12:47.250 align:middle line:84%
were-- it was a
showcase of where,

00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:49.045 align:middle line:84%
perhaps, some
[INAUDIBLE] in humanity

00:12:49.045 --> 00:12:51.820 align:middle line:90%
in this 2012 confusion.

00:12:51.820 --> 00:12:54.820 align:middle line:84%
So what kind of message is that
to give to people coming in,

00:12:54.820 --> 00:12:55.970 align:middle line:90%
the new generation?

00:12:55.970 --> 00:12:58.180 align:middle line:84%
But what I'm saying
is that they're not

00:12:58.180 --> 00:12:59.590 align:middle line:90%
going to pick up on that.

00:12:59.590 --> 00:13:03.266 align:middle line:84%
It's like, well,
that's your thing.

00:13:03.266 --> 00:13:05.690 align:middle line:84%
But the generation
coming in now,

00:13:05.690 --> 00:13:07.640 align:middle line:84%
I feel that they can
have completely a say,

00:13:07.640 --> 00:13:09.098 align:middle line:84%
a different
understanding, which is

00:13:09.098 --> 00:13:13.470 align:middle line:84%
why they had less faith in
the acquired information,

00:13:13.470 --> 00:13:17.500 align:middle line:84%
or less contact with
social conditioning.

00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:21.770 align:middle line:84%
And that's a major factor,
which has slowed down

00:13:21.770 --> 00:13:25.040 align:middle line:84%
a great generational change,
is social conditioning.

00:13:25.040 --> 00:13:28.010 align:middle line:84%
Or another word for that
is social engineering.

00:13:28.010 --> 00:13:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And social engineering
has been a major component

00:13:31.060 --> 00:13:34.830 align:middle line:84%
of human civilization, human
societies, for centuries,

00:13:34.830 --> 00:13:38.690 align:middle line:84%
whether we go back to the
priestly castes centuries ago.

00:13:38.690 --> 00:13:40.190 align:middle line:84%
All the way down
the line, there has

00:13:40.190 --> 00:13:42.640 align:middle line:84%
been institutions
that have tried

00:13:42.640 --> 00:13:45.220 align:middle line:84%
to socially condition the
populous, because that's

00:13:45.220 --> 00:13:48.660 align:middle line:84%
the main thing is
that force for change

00:13:48.660 --> 00:13:50.740 align:middle line:84%
will have to come
through the individuals.

00:13:50.740 --> 00:13:53.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's the tug of war
which is happening now

00:13:53.900 --> 00:13:56.930 align:middle line:84%
in this transition and
which will play out

00:13:56.930 --> 00:13:58.690 align:middle line:84%
in the generation
coming in, this tug

00:13:58.690 --> 00:14:03.970 align:middle line:84%
of war between hierarchical
institutions and the more

00:14:03.970 --> 00:14:07.550 align:middle line:84%
decentralized connectivity
and power and energy

00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:08.710 align:middle line:90%
between the individuals.

00:14:08.710 --> 00:14:11.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's take a moment
and go back even further, just

00:14:11.570 --> 00:14:13.060 align:middle line:90%
a little bit.

00:14:13.060 --> 00:14:16.061 align:middle line:84%
We can't just negate an
entire generation of people.

00:14:16.061 --> 00:14:18.560 align:middle line:84%
There have been advances that
have been made that have maybe

00:14:18.560 --> 00:14:21.410 align:middle line:84%
put some other things in
place they'll have access to,

00:14:21.410 --> 00:14:24.950 align:middle line:84%
by way of our generation and
even our parents' generation.

00:14:24.950 --> 00:14:27.510 align:middle line:84%
So maybe just hopscotch
quickly through that,

00:14:27.510 --> 00:14:31.230 align:middle line:84%
in your mind, what each
one laid foundationally

00:14:31.230 --> 00:14:34.170 align:middle line:84%
for the next that was
really necessary as tools

00:14:34.170 --> 00:14:35.443 align:middle line:90%
for the next one.

00:14:35.443 --> 00:14:36.920 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Sure.

00:14:36.920 --> 00:14:39.660 align:middle line:84%
Very necessary, and we
can't negate it at all.

00:14:39.660 --> 00:14:41.880 align:middle line:84%
There's an Eastern
proverb which says,

00:14:41.880 --> 00:14:44.920 align:middle line:84%
"You will ride your donkey
to the door of your house,

00:14:44.920 --> 00:14:47.080 align:middle line:84%
but you won't ride
it into your house."

00:14:47.080 --> 00:14:50.240 align:middle line:84%
And maybe one layer of
meaning that suggests

00:14:50.240 --> 00:14:53.820 align:middle line:84%
is that we have one vehicle
to get us to one place.

00:14:53.820 --> 00:14:55.360 align:middle line:84%
And then, when
it's time, we need

00:14:55.360 --> 00:14:58.920 align:middle line:84%
to get off and take a different
mode of transport, for example.

00:14:58.920 --> 00:15:01.300 align:middle line:84%
Now, the evolution
of consciousness

00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:05.390 align:middle line:84%
has been increasing
throughout time.

00:15:05.390 --> 00:15:07.210 align:middle line:90%
Now, it may not seem that way.

00:15:07.210 --> 00:15:09.400 align:middle line:84%
If we look at the history
of the 20th century,

00:15:09.400 --> 00:15:12.350 align:middle line:84%
it looks like a history
of warfare, destruction.

00:15:12.350 --> 00:15:14.300 align:middle line:84%
And things have been
going down hill.

00:15:14.300 --> 00:15:16.570 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you look
at the vocabulary

00:15:16.570 --> 00:15:21.870 align:middle line:84%
and the understanding of the
inner world of the human being,

00:15:21.870 --> 00:15:24.650 align:middle line:84%
in fact, there's been
an ongoing increase.

00:15:24.650 --> 00:15:27.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, for example,
if we look at, let's

00:15:27.700 --> 00:15:30.150 align:middle line:84%
say, the second half
of the 19th century,

00:15:30.150 --> 00:15:33.040 align:middle line:84%
we had the growth of the
Transcendentalist movement,

00:15:33.040 --> 00:15:34.690 align:middle line:90%
in America, especially.

00:15:34.690 --> 00:15:37.040 align:middle line:84%
We had the Theosophy
in movement.

00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:40.350 align:middle line:84%
We had the growth in
seances, in people

00:15:40.350 --> 00:15:43.580 align:middle line:84%
trying to connect
with life after death.

00:15:43.580 --> 00:15:46.990 align:middle line:84%
Then we had the
initial stirrings

00:15:46.990 --> 00:15:50.450 align:middle line:84%
of psychiatry and
Freud and Jung.

00:15:50.450 --> 00:15:53.610 align:middle line:84%
And Wilhelm Reich also,
bringing the vocabulary

00:15:53.610 --> 00:15:56.955 align:middle line:84%
of how to access and
understand the inner world.

00:15:56.955 --> 00:16:00.410 align:middle line:84%
Then we had a wave of
teachers and teaching

00:16:00.410 --> 00:16:02.730 align:middle line:84%
coming over into the
West from the East.

00:16:02.730 --> 00:16:05.790 align:middle line:90%
We had Yogananda coming over.

00:16:05.790 --> 00:16:08.080 align:middle line:84%
We had a lot of
other Zen teachings,

00:16:08.080 --> 00:16:10.480 align:middle line:90%
a lot of Sufi teachers.

00:16:10.480 --> 00:16:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And then that went into
the wave of, let's say,

00:16:13.140 --> 00:16:15.700 align:middle line:84%
postwar '50s and
'60s, where there's

00:16:15.700 --> 00:16:19.230 align:middle line:84%
a great deal of experimentalism
with the inner world,

00:16:19.230 --> 00:16:23.200 align:middle line:84%
a great initial contact
with shamanic practices.

00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:25.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exploration of
near-death experiences,

00:16:25.200 --> 00:16:27.280 align:middle line:84%
out of body
experiences, all of it.

00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:27.780 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:16:27.780 --> 00:16:30.380 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Channeling, contact
with other intelligences,

00:16:30.380 --> 00:16:33.530 align:middle line:84%
the growth of the transcendental
psychology movement,

00:16:33.530 --> 00:16:36.660 align:middle line:84%
meditation-- and so
for example, if we

00:16:36.660 --> 00:16:39.950 align:middle line:84%
spoke with our grandparents
and said, oh, sorry,

00:16:39.950 --> 00:16:41.604 align:middle line:90%
I had a Freudian slip.

00:16:41.604 --> 00:16:44.020 align:middle line:84%
Our grandparents would probably
answer, well, who's Freud,

00:16:44.020 --> 00:16:45.810 align:middle line:90%
and where did he slip?

00:16:45.810 --> 00:16:48.280 align:middle line:84%
Because they didn't have
that vocabulary or language

00:16:48.280 --> 00:16:51.760 align:middle line:84%
to try to reflect
upon the inner world.

00:16:51.760 --> 00:16:54.800 align:middle line:84%
So if we look at the inner
world different from what

00:16:54.800 --> 00:16:56.810 align:middle line:84%
we see in propaganda
from the outer world--

00:16:56.810 --> 00:16:57.893 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Externally, yes.

00:16:57.893 --> 00:17:00.300 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: --we see,
in fact, a revolution

00:17:00.300 --> 00:17:03.260 align:middle line:84%
that's been ongoing
in how we access

00:17:03.260 --> 00:17:06.319 align:middle line:84%
and how we experiment and come
to understand the inner world.

00:17:06.319 --> 00:17:11.280 align:middle line:84%
And now I feel that's coming
more convergent in how we then

00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:12.804 align:middle line:90%
deal with the outer world.

00:17:12.804 --> 00:17:14.220 align:middle line:84%
We're bringing
them together, just

00:17:14.220 --> 00:17:16.260 align:middle line:84%
like science and spirituality
is coming together

00:17:16.260 --> 00:17:17.900 align:middle line:90%
in the fields of knowledge.

00:17:17.900 --> 00:17:19.405 align:middle line:84%
So too, I feel,
is the expression

00:17:19.405 --> 00:17:21.310 align:middle line:84%
of the inner world
coming together

00:17:21.310 --> 00:17:23.245 align:middle line:84%
with how we deal in
our everyday life.

00:17:23.245 --> 00:17:25.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we did,
on an external level,

00:17:25.630 --> 00:17:29.940 align:middle line:84%
bring forth, as you said in
your book, unprecedented growth,

00:17:29.940 --> 00:17:31.960 align:middle line:90%
technological advancement.

00:17:31.960 --> 00:17:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And part of this
technological advancement

00:17:34.360 --> 00:17:37.140 align:middle line:84%
leads us to the way-- the means
by which people are watching

00:17:37.140 --> 00:17:39.910 align:middle line:84%
this today-- the
connectivity of online media,

00:17:39.910 --> 00:17:42.010 align:middle line:84%
for example, which
brings us more

00:17:42.010 --> 00:17:45.690 align:middle line:84%
to the subject of transparency,
as another example.

00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:49.080 align:middle line:84%
And these-- as you were saying
in the book, up until now,

00:17:49.080 --> 00:17:51.000 align:middle line:84%
we all lead relatively
compartmentalized

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:54.230 align:middle line:84%
lives-- regions, countries,
states, neighborhoods.

00:17:54.230 --> 00:17:56.830 align:middle line:90%
Now, it's all connected.

00:17:56.830 --> 00:18:01.220 align:middle line:84%
And this is the medium to which
these children are being born.

00:18:01.220 --> 00:18:04.810 align:middle line:84%
And this is interesting,
because our generation

00:18:04.810 --> 00:18:10.080 align:middle line:84%
is suspicious of that degree
of connectivity, even Facebook,

00:18:10.080 --> 00:18:11.300 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:18:11.300 --> 00:18:14.290 align:middle line:84%
Who wants everyone to know
all of their data, everything

00:18:14.290 --> 00:18:17.230 align:middle line:84%
they're doing, kind of the
eye on the sky mentality?

00:18:17.230 --> 00:18:19.970 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about the interface
between that and then the newer

00:18:19.970 --> 00:18:22.490 align:middle line:84%
generation and how they're
going to feel about it,

00:18:22.490 --> 00:18:24.500 align:middle line:84%
being bathed in
transparency from day one.

00:18:24.500 --> 00:18:27.700 align:middle line:84%
>> DENNIS: That's a
huge question, Regina.

00:18:27.700 --> 00:18:31.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Take your time.

00:18:31.290 --> 00:18:34.204 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: The world is
shifting now into different--

00:18:34.204 --> 00:18:37.320 align:middle line:84%
a different temporal-spatial
environment.

00:18:37.320 --> 00:18:40.120 align:middle line:84%
So for example-- and
this, again, as you say,

00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:44.540 align:middle line:84%
owes a great debt to the process
of the Industrial Revolution,

00:18:44.540 --> 00:18:47.770 align:middle line:84%
bringing in the radio,
the television, which

00:18:47.770 --> 00:18:51.510 align:middle line:84%
started to bring in different
forms of time and space

00:18:51.510 --> 00:18:53.840 align:middle line:90%
for our parents or grandparents.

00:18:53.840 --> 00:18:56.530 align:middle line:84%
But it was mostly
one-on-one, one-way.

00:18:56.530 --> 00:18:57.920 align:middle line:90%
And we were receivers.

00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:01.210 align:middle line:84%
So it developed a
consumerist environment,

00:19:01.210 --> 00:19:03.270 align:middle line:90%
where we received information.

00:19:03.270 --> 00:19:08.000 align:middle line:84%
Now, we're on the cusp
off putting in place

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:11.850 align:middle line:84%
the initial mechanisms
or initial birth

00:19:11.850 --> 00:19:15.820 align:middle line:84%
pains of moving towards
a planetary society.

00:19:15.820 --> 00:19:18.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, that may put a lot of
fear into people by saying,

00:19:18.240 --> 00:19:22.450 align:middle line:84%
oh, planetary society, one
world government, the Borg,

00:19:22.450 --> 00:19:23.910 align:middle line:90%
et cetera.

00:19:23.910 --> 00:19:25.220 align:middle line:90%
That's understandable.

00:19:25.220 --> 00:19:28.090 align:middle line:84%
Because when something
new comes in, of course,

00:19:28.090 --> 00:19:29.950 align:middle line:84%
the incumbent power
structures wish

00:19:29.950 --> 00:19:32.450 align:middle line:84%
to appropriate it
for their own use.

00:19:32.450 --> 00:19:35.220 align:middle line:90%
So we see the surveillance.

00:19:35.220 --> 00:19:38.202 align:middle line:84%
We see the NSA, National
Security Agency.

00:19:38.202 --> 00:19:40.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, walking down
the streets of London-- CCTV

00:19:40.810 --> 00:19:41.840 align:middle line:90%
cameras everywhere.

00:19:41.840 --> 00:19:44.352 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: The most
CCTV city in the world.

00:19:44.352 --> 00:19:45.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: My god.

00:19:45.060 --> 00:19:47.360 align:middle line:84%
You can't walk down the
street without being on film.

00:19:47.360 --> 00:19:49.400 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: So our
generation as well, we

00:19:49.400 --> 00:19:53.940 align:middle line:84%
have that fear of, well,
this is not good for us.

00:19:53.940 --> 00:19:55.500 align:middle line:84%
Another thing we're
noticing, though,

00:19:55.500 --> 00:19:59.120 align:middle line:84%
is that as we're become
more connected in the world,

00:19:59.120 --> 00:20:02.570 align:middle line:84%
that time and space
interaction is actually

00:20:02.570 --> 00:20:04.720 align:middle line:90%
creating a response nueronally.

00:20:04.720 --> 00:20:07.960 align:middle line:84%
And the young children are
being rewired differently.

00:20:07.960 --> 00:20:11.260 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's a wonderful
quote that goes back

00:20:11.260 --> 00:20:14.940 align:middle line:84%
to the 13th century from
the great Persian poet Rumi,

00:20:14.940 --> 00:20:16.330 align:middle line:90%
Mewlana.

00:20:16.330 --> 00:20:19.720 align:middle line:84%
And Rumi said that, "New
organs of perception

00:20:19.720 --> 00:20:22.610 align:middle line:84%
come into being
according to necessity.

00:20:22.610 --> 00:20:25.355 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, oh human,
increase your necessity."

00:20:25.355 --> 00:20:26.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it's beautiful.

00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:29.990 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And so the
necessity is coming in now.

00:20:29.990 --> 00:20:31.880 align:middle line:84%
And so-- I mean,
there's many instances--

00:20:31.880 --> 00:20:34.380 align:middle line:84%
we can talk about that later--
of how the young children are

00:20:34.380 --> 00:20:36.680 align:middle line:84%
being more tactile
and more empathic.

00:20:36.680 --> 00:20:40.380 align:middle line:84%
So now, how do we look
at that perspective?

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:42.430 align:middle line:84%
Now, we can have the
fear perspective,

00:20:42.430 --> 00:20:46.720 align:middle line:84%
which is what the incumbent
powers wish to play out.

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:47.840 align:middle line:90%
Be careful of technology.

00:20:47.840 --> 00:20:50.510 align:middle line:84%
Be careful of the
globalization-- which

00:20:50.510 --> 00:20:53.350 align:middle line:84%
was a neo-liberal
project-- because it's

00:20:53.350 --> 00:20:55.070 align:middle line:90%
going to control you.

00:20:55.070 --> 00:20:57.490 align:middle line:84%
The question is,
though-- is it going

00:20:57.490 --> 00:21:00.750 align:middle line:84%
to control or be able to control
a new consciousness, which

00:21:00.750 --> 00:21:03.800 align:middle line:84%
is coming in and is going to
be using these technologies

00:21:03.800 --> 00:21:04.917 align:middle line:90%
in a different way.

00:21:04.917 --> 00:21:06.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Talk about that.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:09.240 align:middle line:84%
Talk about how you see
that technology being used,

00:21:09.240 --> 00:21:11.980 align:middle line:84%
say, 10 years out,
when these kids

00:21:11.980 --> 00:21:14.340 align:middle line:84%
are coming into their
teenage years and such.

00:21:14.340 --> 00:21:16.000 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Well, in
one sense, we're

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:19.115 align:middle line:84%
seeing the early signs
of that with the protest

00:21:19.115 --> 00:21:21.240 align:middle line:84%
revolutions around the
world, with the Arab Spring,

00:21:21.240 --> 00:21:23.650 align:middle line:84%
for example, and the Jasmine
Revolution, that they

00:21:23.650 --> 00:21:28.640 align:middle line:84%
used technologies to bypass the
communications when the state

00:21:28.640 --> 00:21:30.720 align:middle line:84%
authorities cut
the communications.

00:21:30.720 --> 00:21:33.370 align:middle line:90%
So they're very tech savvy.

00:21:33.370 --> 00:21:36.030 align:middle line:84%
But also, it's the
way of collaborating.

00:21:36.030 --> 00:21:38.600 align:middle line:84%
It's that, like you
said previously,

00:21:38.600 --> 00:21:42.410 align:middle line:84%
we've been conditioned to have
a compartmentalized view of life

00:21:42.410 --> 00:21:44.550 align:middle line:84%
and a compartmentalized
behaviorism,

00:21:44.550 --> 00:21:47.830 align:middle line:84%
because that helps
the nation-states.

00:21:47.830 --> 00:21:54.060 align:middle line:84%
That helps to support this
divided world-- them versus us.

00:21:54.060 --> 00:21:56.080 align:middle line:84%
But the empathic
consciousness, which

00:21:56.080 --> 00:21:59.600 align:middle line:84%
is going to be empowered
through this collaborative,

00:21:59.600 --> 00:22:02.980 align:middle line:84%
connective society, that
empathic consciousness is not

00:22:02.980 --> 00:22:05.290 align:middle line:84%
going to feel-- not
going to feel into

00:22:05.290 --> 00:22:09.050 align:middle line:84%
or even play out the
same them versus us.

00:22:09.050 --> 00:22:12.480 align:middle line:84%
So if we look at, for
example, manifestations

00:22:12.480 --> 00:22:13.890 align:middle line:90%
in the Middle East.

00:22:13.890 --> 00:22:16.160 align:middle line:84%
Now, the big players,
the older generation

00:22:16.160 --> 00:22:19.630 align:middle line:84%
or what I call the old guard,
they're standing up and saying,

00:22:19.630 --> 00:22:21.750 align:middle line:84%
we have to be at war
with these people.

00:22:21.750 --> 00:22:22.949 align:middle line:90%
They're against us.

00:22:22.949 --> 00:22:24.990 align:middle line:84%
What they're not showing
us is the younger people

00:22:24.990 --> 00:22:26.020 align:middle line:90%
on the ground.

00:22:26.020 --> 00:22:26.980 align:middle line:90%
They want peace.

00:22:26.980 --> 00:22:28.480 align:middle line:90%
They want to connect.

00:22:28.480 --> 00:22:31.480 align:middle line:84%
And so they're using
social networking

00:22:31.480 --> 00:22:35.495 align:middle line:84%
to connect with others, like
minded, across the barriers

00:22:35.495 --> 00:22:38.800 align:middle line:84%
or across the so-called
artificial barriers.

00:22:38.800 --> 00:22:40.150 align:middle line:90%
And they're reaching out.

00:22:40.150 --> 00:22:42.530 align:middle line:90%
So it's a different level.

00:22:42.530 --> 00:22:45.640 align:middle line:84%
It's a decentralized,
distributed connectivity

00:22:45.640 --> 00:22:47.180 align:middle line:84%
which is coming
in, and that is--

00:22:47.180 --> 00:22:49.795 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA:
Decentralization, keyword.

00:22:49.795 --> 00:22:52.285 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And empathic
consciousness as well.

00:22:52.285 --> 00:22:54.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which is
interesting, because we're

00:22:54.160 --> 00:22:58.850 align:middle line:84%
talking about global structures,
global governments, perhaps

00:22:58.850 --> 00:23:02.930 align:middle line:84%
even global economies,
and decentralization

00:23:02.930 --> 00:23:04.400 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:05.024 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:23:05.024 --> 00:23:06.815 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: It's the two
agendas playing out.

00:23:06.815 --> 00:23:07.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:23:07.820 --> 00:23:11.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: For example, we're
at the end of empires now.

00:23:11.660 --> 00:23:13.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:23:13.060 --> 00:23:15.300 align:middle line:84%
Yours went down, and
now ours is going down.

00:23:15.300 --> 00:23:17.910 align:middle line:90%


00:23:17.910 --> 00:23:19.180 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: The boat is sinking.

00:23:19.180 --> 00:23:19.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:23:19.770 --> 00:23:23.332 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: You see, let's take
the metaphor of drowning.

00:23:23.332 --> 00:23:28.120 align:middle line:84%
A drowning person is a
person who struggles more.

00:23:28.120 --> 00:23:29.820 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they say,
be careful if you go

00:23:29.820 --> 00:23:31.370 align:middle line:84%
and try to save a
drowning person,

00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:33.090 align:middle line:84%
because they may take
you down with them.

00:23:33.090 --> 00:23:34.920 align:middle line:84%
Because they're struggling,
and they're struggling.

00:23:34.920 --> 00:23:36.336 align:middle line:84%
And they're in
their death throes.

00:23:36.336 --> 00:23:38.270 align:middle line:84%
And it's a dangerous
place to be.

00:23:38.270 --> 00:23:41.030 align:middle line:84%
So now, people
may say, well, you

00:23:41.030 --> 00:23:42.980 align:middle line:84%
have a positive
view of the future.

00:23:42.980 --> 00:23:45.010 align:middle line:84%
But what about what
we see in the world?

00:23:45.010 --> 00:23:47.970 align:middle line:84%
My response is, well, I'm
looking at the long term.

00:23:47.970 --> 00:23:50.810 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the
shorter term, then we're

00:23:50.810 --> 00:23:53.940 align:middle line:84%
seeing these death throes,
which are quite dangerous.

00:23:53.940 --> 00:23:57.817 align:middle line:84%
And they are creating the
disruption and the disharmony.

00:23:57.817 --> 00:23:59.347 align:middle line:90%
And they're the negative energy.

00:23:59.347 --> 00:24:00.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But they're
quite necessary.

00:24:00.930 --> 00:24:03.702 align:middle line:84%
It's just a part of
the process of change.

00:24:03.702 --> 00:24:07.270 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And again, I think
humanity, by our very nature,

00:24:07.270 --> 00:24:11.770 align:middle line:84%
has a short term-- history
of short-term view.

00:24:11.770 --> 00:24:14.430 align:middle line:84%
If we look back at the
history of civilizations--

00:24:14.430 --> 00:24:17.470 align:middle line:84%
and forgive me, because my
background is sociology.

00:24:17.470 --> 00:24:21.180 align:middle line:84%
I did come through
that academic field.

00:24:21.180 --> 00:24:23.880 align:middle line:84%
And we see how
civilizations, they

00:24:23.880 --> 00:24:26.090 align:middle line:90%
go through a rise and a fall.

00:24:26.090 --> 00:24:28.790 align:middle line:84%
But in fact often when
they're taking over,

00:24:28.790 --> 00:24:31.910 align:middle line:84%
the new power that comes in
doesn't come from the center.

00:24:31.910 --> 00:24:34.190 align:middle line:90%
It comes from the periphery.

00:24:34.190 --> 00:24:37.230 align:middle line:84%
Because the center tries to
hold out, tries to hold out,

00:24:37.230 --> 00:24:40.860 align:middle line:84%
tries to centralize their
power, but they can no longer

00:24:40.860 --> 00:24:43.810 align:middle line:84%
maintain a coherence
with the periphery.

00:24:43.810 --> 00:24:45.890 align:middle line:84%
And so they fold, and
the new energies--

00:24:45.890 --> 00:24:49.130 align:middle line:84%
such as the fall of Rome was
because the Visigoths came in

00:24:49.130 --> 00:24:50.610 align:middle line:90%
from the periphery.

00:24:50.610 --> 00:24:53.325 align:middle line:84%
Now, what I'm saying is that
the individuals of this world

00:24:53.325 --> 00:24:55.790 align:middle line:84%
are going to come in
from the periphery,

00:24:55.790 --> 00:24:59.045 align:middle line:84%
and they're going to be
connected like never before.

00:24:59.045 --> 00:25:00.640 align:middle line:84%
And that is why
there's a greater

00:25:00.640 --> 00:25:01.940 align:middle line:90%
fear with the authorities.

00:25:01.940 --> 00:25:04.680 align:middle line:84%
Because they see it
coming, and they don't know

00:25:04.680 --> 00:25:05.600 align:middle line:90%
how to deal with it.

00:25:05.600 --> 00:25:08.250 align:middle line:84%
Their only response,
with the old mind,

00:25:08.250 --> 00:25:12.050 align:middle line:84%
is to increase the
centralized power structures.

00:25:12.050 --> 00:25:14.810 align:middle line:84%
It's an old paradigm
response, but it's not

00:25:14.810 --> 00:25:16.804 align:middle line:84%
going to play out
in the long term

00:25:16.804 --> 00:25:18.470 align:middle line:84%
because it can't hold
off the periphery.

00:25:18.470 --> 00:25:21.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It can't hold,
because it's actually

00:25:21.000 --> 00:25:24.200 align:middle line:84%
a wholesale shift
in consciousness

00:25:24.200 --> 00:25:28.420 align:middle line:84%
by that point, in which the
people aren't fearing other.

00:25:28.420 --> 00:25:31.260 align:middle line:84%
They've been connected
with-- kids in UK

00:25:31.260 --> 00:25:33.990 align:middle line:84%
have been connected with
the kids in the Ukraine

00:25:33.990 --> 00:25:35.760 align:middle line:90%
during all of this.

00:25:35.760 --> 00:25:38.094 align:middle line:84%
They're learning about
each other's strife,

00:25:38.094 --> 00:25:39.260 align:middle line:90%
in friendships and so forth.

00:25:39.260 --> 00:25:40.740 align:middle line:90%
But let's go beyond that.

00:25:40.740 --> 00:25:43.370 align:middle line:84%
As you say, this
generation is going

00:25:43.370 --> 00:25:45.080 align:middle line:84%
to be more empathic
and more intuitive,

00:25:45.080 --> 00:25:47.320 align:middle line:84%
meaning the senses,
our finer senses,

00:25:47.320 --> 00:25:51.260 align:middle line:84%
will be opening up, beginning
with-- and en masse-- beginning

00:25:51.260 --> 00:25:53.700 align:middle line:84%
with that generation,
meaning there

00:25:53.700 --> 00:25:55.900 align:middle line:84%
is no such thing as
compartmentalization.

00:25:55.900 --> 00:25:58.900 align:middle line:90%
You can't hide.

00:25:58.900 --> 00:26:01.530 align:middle line:84%
In that sense, that's
where-- I don't like the fact

00:26:01.530 --> 00:26:03.980 align:middle line:84%
that my data is all over
the place on the computer,

00:26:03.980 --> 00:26:06.730 align:middle line:84%
and agencies and
whoever might have that.

00:26:06.730 --> 00:26:09.270 align:middle line:84%
But the reality
is, they're more--

00:26:09.270 --> 00:26:11.440 align:middle line:84%
there's nothing to hide
because you can't hide.

00:26:11.440 --> 00:26:14.240 align:middle line:84%
If you have those kinds of
instincts highly developed,

00:26:14.240 --> 00:26:15.130 align:middle line:90%
what's to hide?

00:26:15.130 --> 00:26:18.740 align:middle line:84%
You can't hide from that
degree of consciousness.

00:26:18.740 --> 00:26:22.707 align:middle line:84%
You can't hide from that
visibility with others, right?

00:26:22.707 --> 00:26:23.540 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: It's true.

00:26:23.540 --> 00:26:26.540 align:middle line:84%
And that's exactly-- again,
that's our social conditioning

00:26:26.540 --> 00:26:29.972 align:middle line:84%
is the fear of this
information coming out.

00:26:29.972 --> 00:26:31.930 align:middle line:84%
But the key word I think
you mentioned earlier,

00:26:31.930 --> 00:26:34.070 align:middle line:90%
Regina, is transparency.

00:26:34.070 --> 00:26:36.565 align:middle line:84%
Is that the transparency--
our generation

00:26:36.565 --> 00:26:39.560 align:middle line:84%
is still uncomfortable
with that.

00:26:39.560 --> 00:26:42.120 align:middle line:84%
And of course, it
plays into the system.

00:26:42.120 --> 00:26:45.084 align:middle line:84%
It plays into politics,
where everything is cloaked.

00:26:45.084 --> 00:26:46.750 align:middle line:84%
Everything is the
emperor's new clothes.

00:26:46.750 --> 00:26:47.333 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:26:47.333 --> 00:26:49.890 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And our generation--
and previously more

00:26:49.890 --> 00:26:54.120 align:middle line:84%
so-- is that we did not
want to question that.

00:26:54.120 --> 00:26:56.800 align:middle line:90%
We were hesitant to question it.

00:26:56.800 --> 00:26:59.600 align:middle line:84%
We had what we call
obedience to authority.

00:26:59.600 --> 00:27:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And we can refer to the great
Stanley Milgram experiment

00:27:02.690 --> 00:27:06.950 align:middle line:84%
about how we follow authority
if someone wears a lab coat.

00:27:06.950 --> 00:27:09.520 align:middle line:84%
We see someone on television
wearing a white coat saying,

00:27:09.520 --> 00:27:11.040 align:middle line:90%
this washing powder is the best.

00:27:11.040 --> 00:27:12.860 align:middle line:90%
We believe them.

00:27:12.860 --> 00:27:13.650 align:middle line:90%
The shift is--

00:27:13.650 --> 00:27:15.740 align:middle line:84%
One of the major
shifts taking place

00:27:15.740 --> 00:27:20.140 align:middle line:84%
is that automatic conditioning
is not going to apply.

00:27:20.140 --> 00:27:22.110 align:middle line:84%
And so we're going
to come to a syndrome

00:27:22.110 --> 00:27:24.180 align:middle line:84%
where the emperor
is really going

00:27:24.180 --> 00:27:25.600 align:middle line:84%
to be seen for
having no clothes.

00:27:25.600 --> 00:27:27.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, we all are.

00:27:27.240 --> 00:27:29.320 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that what
we're all afraid of?

00:27:29.320 --> 00:27:31.020 align:middle line:90%
That's the interesting thing.

00:27:31.020 --> 00:27:34.150 align:middle line:84%
The newer generation-- the kids
that are now in their teens,

00:27:34.150 --> 00:27:36.510 align:middle line:84%
for example, even into their
'20s, and then of course

00:27:36.510 --> 00:27:39.400 align:middle line:84%
younger-- don't seem
to have any fear

00:27:39.400 --> 00:27:42.030 align:middle line:90%
of being seen for who they are.

00:27:42.030 --> 00:27:44.980 align:middle line:84%
And they'll put their worst
behavior out there, even,

00:27:44.980 --> 00:27:46.860 align:middle line:84%
where our generation
is still looking

00:27:46.860 --> 00:27:50.680 align:middle line:84%
at not being seen for the flawed
humans that we actually are.

00:27:50.680 --> 00:27:53.710 align:middle line:84%
This is a huge
psychological shift,

00:27:53.710 --> 00:27:57.870 align:middle line:84%
to move from hiding our
flaws to allowing ourselves

00:27:57.870 --> 00:28:00.045 align:middle line:90%
to be so publicly visible.

00:28:00.045 --> 00:28:01.190 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yeah.

00:28:01.190 --> 00:28:04.800 align:middle line:84%
And it's also a question
of digital identity.

00:28:04.800 --> 00:28:06.791 align:middle line:84%
It's something completely
new for many of us

00:28:06.791 --> 00:28:07.790 align:middle line:90%
in the older generation.

00:28:07.790 --> 00:28:09.790 align:middle line:90%
What is digital identity?

00:28:09.790 --> 00:28:11.840 align:middle line:84%
Because we've been living
in a physical world.

00:28:11.840 --> 00:28:15.550 align:middle line:84%
Now we're moving towards a
convergence of the inner world,

00:28:15.550 --> 00:28:18.830 align:middle line:84%
the outer world, and a
technological world as well.

00:28:18.830 --> 00:28:23.070 align:middle line:84%
And so we will need to
navigate all of that.

00:28:23.070 --> 00:28:24.850 align:middle line:90%
And for us, it's difficult.

00:28:24.850 --> 00:28:25.814 align:middle line:90%
We have that fear.

00:28:25.814 --> 00:28:27.230 align:middle line:84%
Now, the younger
generations, they

00:28:27.230 --> 00:28:29.300 align:middle line:84%
don't have that fear,
because they sense it.

00:28:29.300 --> 00:28:30.320 align:middle line:90%
They pick it up.

00:28:30.320 --> 00:28:31.820 align:middle line:84%
They pick it up
because they haven't

00:28:31.820 --> 00:28:33.510 align:middle line:90%
known anything different.

00:28:33.510 --> 00:28:36.210 align:middle line:84%
Now, a major point is
that this generation

00:28:36.210 --> 00:28:41.020 align:middle line:84%
will be the first generation
being born into a world where

00:28:41.020 --> 00:28:42.754 align:middle line:84%
it's already set
up technologically

00:28:42.754 --> 00:28:44.420 align:middle line:84%
with the internet,
virtual technologies.

00:28:44.420 --> 00:28:45.586 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The consciousness.

00:28:45.586 --> 00:28:47.020 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yeah.

00:28:47.020 --> 00:28:49.490 align:middle line:84%
And so before-- previous
generations still

00:28:49.490 --> 00:28:51.320 align:middle line:84%
had to learn
something, navigate it.

00:28:51.320 --> 00:28:54.980 align:middle line:84%
And so the energetic
environment,

00:28:54.980 --> 00:28:57.090 align:middle line:84%
with the phoenix generation
we're moving into,

00:28:57.090 --> 00:28:59.800 align:middle line:84%
will seem organic
and natural to them.

00:28:59.800 --> 00:29:01.340 align:middle line:90%
And that's an important point.

00:29:01.340 --> 00:29:03.422 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And more non-linear.

00:29:03.422 --> 00:29:05.380 align:middle line:84%
That's another point you
bring up in your book.

00:29:05.380 --> 00:29:08.505 align:middle line:84%
Their reality will be a
more nonlinear reality.

00:29:08.505 --> 00:29:12.130 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And their
brain, for example, which

00:29:12.130 --> 00:29:13.930 align:middle line:90%
is only just one small organ.

00:29:13.930 --> 00:29:17.206 align:middle line:10%
The mind is the extended
mind, the whole body.

