and how do we channel it?

00:38:50.890 --> 00:38:52.270 align:middle line:90%
And who does it go to?

00:38:52.270 --> 00:38:55.230 align:middle line:84%
So in fact, there isn't
really the scarcity model

00:38:55.230 --> 00:38:57.020 align:middle line:90%
there at all.

00:38:57.020 --> 00:38:58.570 align:middle line:84%
That's been, I think,
an artificial--

00:38:58.570 --> 00:38:59.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Artificially
constructed.

00:38:59.360 --> 00:39:00.850 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Smoke screen.

00:39:00.850 --> 00:39:02.855 align:middle line:84%
But we still need time
to break away from it.

00:39:02.855 --> 00:39:04.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But even when
you talk about-- I mean,

00:39:04.620 --> 00:39:06.580 align:middle line:84%
an interface might be,
as you mentioned before,

00:39:06.580 --> 00:39:07.660 align:middle line:90%
crowd funding.

00:39:07.660 --> 00:39:10.310 align:middle line:84%
With crowd funding,
we feel as though we

00:39:10.310 --> 00:39:13.310 align:middle line:84%
are empowered in that we're
aligning with our own choices,

00:39:13.310 --> 00:39:15.420 align:middle line:84%
rather than what we're
being led toward.

00:39:15.420 --> 00:39:17.630 align:middle line:84%
So that's just the
beginning of being

00:39:17.630 --> 00:39:19.760 align:middle line:84%
able to use a
couple dollars here,

00:39:19.760 --> 00:39:21.400 align:middle line:84%
a couple dollars
there to support

00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:23.150 align:middle line:90%
what we're in alignment with.

00:39:23.150 --> 00:39:26.170 align:middle line:84%
And they come into a world where
that is how they're living.

00:39:26.170 --> 00:39:27.790 align:middle line:84%
In general, that's
how they're living.

00:39:27.790 --> 00:39:29.950 align:middle line:84%
You were talking about--
the modern civilization

00:39:29.950 --> 00:39:32.560 align:middle line:84%
we know now, in
contrast to that,

00:39:32.560 --> 00:39:35.400 align:middle line:84%
has created an
infantile state of mind.

00:39:35.400 --> 00:39:36.626 align:middle line:90%
What did you mean by that?

00:39:36.626 --> 00:39:38.250 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: What I
meant by that, Regina,

00:39:38.250 --> 00:39:43.450 align:middle line:84%
is that we've been conditioned
to have a form of dependency

00:39:43.450 --> 00:39:46.270 align:middle line:90%
and to have the fear of freedom.

00:39:46.270 --> 00:39:49.540 align:middle line:84%
Now, it sounds contradictory,
but one of the greatest fears

00:39:49.540 --> 00:39:51.910 align:middle line:84%
that we've been dealing
with is freedom,

00:39:51.910 --> 00:39:57.470 align:middle line:84%
because we've grown up within
a control mechanism, a control

00:39:57.470 --> 00:40:00.800 align:middle line:84%
matrix, where dependency
is at the forefront.

00:40:00.800 --> 00:40:05.065 align:middle line:84%
Now, whether it's-- because
the exploitation there is

00:40:05.065 --> 00:40:08.120 align:middle line:84%
because, biologically, when
the human being is born,

00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:10.480 align:middle line:84%
it's dependent upon the
mother or the guardian.

00:40:10.480 --> 00:40:13.960 align:middle line:84%
Now, the human being
actually, as a social animal,

00:40:13.960 --> 00:40:16.780 align:middle line:84%
requires a greater
length of dependency

00:40:16.780 --> 00:40:18.160 align:middle line:90%
than most other animals.

00:40:18.160 --> 00:40:21.300 align:middle line:84%
Most other animals, they
have an instinct which

00:40:21.300 --> 00:40:24.080 align:middle line:84%
they can be independent in a
very short time-- human beings,

00:40:24.080 --> 00:40:24.830 align:middle line:90%
no.

00:40:24.830 --> 00:40:27.740 align:middle line:84%
One of the reasons
is that a human being

00:40:27.740 --> 00:40:35.300 align:middle line:84%
is born with less time to
develop, because of the way

00:40:35.300 --> 00:40:37.692 align:middle line:84%
it's given birth,
the birth canal.

00:40:37.692 --> 00:40:39.150 align:middle line:84%
So the brain isn't
fully developed.

00:40:39.150 --> 00:40:41.540 align:middle line:84%
The nervous system
isn't fully developed.

00:40:41.540 --> 00:40:44.040 align:middle line:84%
So the brain of a young
child and the nervous system

00:40:44.040 --> 00:40:46.830 align:middle line:84%
of a young child
completes its development

00:40:46.830 --> 00:40:48.640 align:middle line:90%
in social atmosphere.

00:40:48.640 --> 00:40:51.300 align:middle line:84%
So that dependency's
is the first stage.

00:40:51.300 --> 00:40:56.570 align:middle line:84%
When that is then taken to
further degrees deliberately

00:40:56.570 --> 00:40:58.650 align:middle line:84%
and, for example,
have dependency

00:40:58.650 --> 00:41:04.220 align:middle line:84%
on maybe our peers, our
teachers, anyone in a uniform.

00:41:04.220 --> 00:41:06.890 align:middle line:84%
Now, the economic system
has developed that,

00:41:06.890 --> 00:41:08.035 align:middle line:90%
that we have dependency.

00:41:08.035 --> 00:41:09.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, take
it all the way

00:41:09.410 --> 00:41:11.760 align:middle line:84%
through to your last
breath, that you

00:41:11.760 --> 00:41:17.050 align:middle line:84%
work for-- starting at age 23
toward a pension of dependency

00:41:17.050 --> 00:41:18.700 align:middle line:90%
on a system.

00:41:18.700 --> 00:41:20.352 align:middle line:90%
Soul killing.

00:41:20.352 --> 00:41:22.050 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: If we say
to people, well,

00:41:22.050 --> 00:41:24.060 align:middle line:84%
if you want to change
your priorities,

00:41:24.060 --> 00:41:25.680 align:middle line:90%
change your life patterns.

00:41:25.680 --> 00:41:26.890 align:middle line:90%
Change your country.

00:41:26.890 --> 00:41:30.050 align:middle line:84%
And people will say,
well, wonderful advice.

00:41:30.050 --> 00:41:31.660 align:middle line:90%
But I have a mortgage.

00:41:31.660 --> 00:41:33.950 align:middle line:90%
I have a debt with the bank.

00:41:33.950 --> 00:41:36.310 align:middle line:84%
I can't move away
from my job because I

00:41:36.310 --> 00:41:39.290 align:middle line:84%
have to pay my credit
every month or my mortgage.

00:41:39.290 --> 00:41:41.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that's
our generation.

00:41:41.420 --> 00:41:44.542 align:middle line:84%
That's not going to be
their generation, per se.

00:41:44.542 --> 00:41:46.750 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: I think they're
not going to buy into that.

00:41:46.750 --> 00:41:47.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:41:47.180 --> 00:41:49.388 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Because they're
going to see it a mile off.

00:41:49.388 --> 00:41:50.105 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yay.

00:41:50.105 --> 00:41:51.896 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Because the
worst thing we can do

00:41:51.896 --> 00:41:54.379 align:middle line:84%
is give away our power, give
away our inner authority.

00:41:54.379 --> 00:41:55.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And what
you say about that

00:41:55.920 --> 00:41:58.270 align:middle line:84%
is, when you're caught
in the old dynamic

00:41:58.270 --> 00:42:02.820 align:middle line:84%
that we are in, which is that
lack and fear based culture--

00:42:02.820 --> 00:42:06.840 align:middle line:84%
globally, pretty much--
it creates responses that

00:42:06.840 --> 00:42:11.740 align:middle line:84%
are extreme in nature, a
need for extreme feeling,

00:42:11.740 --> 00:42:15.320 align:middle line:84%
for violent sports,
and so forth.

00:42:15.320 --> 00:42:19.480 align:middle line:84%
You're saying that, again,
is what that generation will

00:42:19.480 --> 00:42:21.240 align:middle line:90%
be moving away from.

00:42:21.240 --> 00:42:21.930 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yes.

00:42:21.930 --> 00:42:24.827 align:middle line:84%
I mean, violent sports, for
example, a sense of extreme.

00:42:24.827 --> 00:42:26.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Part of
the repression, yes.

00:42:26.410 --> 00:42:30.930 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: That extreme
release is a human need

00:42:30.930 --> 00:42:36.350 align:middle line:84%
as a counterbalance to
this internal constriction.

00:42:36.350 --> 00:42:41.330 align:middle line:84%
Now, for example, we hear
stories of, for example,

00:42:41.330 --> 00:42:42.260 align:middle line:90%
rock stars.

00:42:42.260 --> 00:42:43.410 align:middle line:90%
They go into hotels.

00:42:43.410 --> 00:42:44.880 align:middle line:90%
They smash TVs.

00:42:44.880 --> 00:42:48.350 align:middle line:84%
They think, oh, this
extremism, society loves it.

00:42:48.350 --> 00:42:51.470 align:middle line:84%
And young people think, this is
a wonderful sense of freedom.

00:42:51.470 --> 00:42:53.550 align:middle line:84%
What they don't
realize is that they

00:42:53.550 --> 00:42:55.250 align:middle line:90%
do that to sell more records.

00:42:55.250 --> 00:42:57.680 align:middle line:84%
It's encouraged by
the record industry.

00:42:57.680 --> 00:42:59.070 align:middle line:90%
It's all playing the game.

00:42:59.070 --> 00:43:01.830 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, speaking
of playing the game,

00:43:01.830 --> 00:43:05.020 align:middle line:84%
a couple days ago, we were
walking down the street

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.010 align:middle line:90%
here in Chelsea.

00:43:06.010 --> 00:43:07.830 align:middle line:84%
And Chelsea had
just won a football,

00:43:07.830 --> 00:43:10.010 align:middle line:90%
or soccer match in our parlance.

00:43:10.010 --> 00:43:12.650 align:middle line:84%
Oh, my god, it's
frightening being there.

00:43:12.650 --> 00:43:16.610 align:middle line:84%
People had their flip
cams and their cell phones

00:43:16.610 --> 00:43:19.820 align:middle line:84%
taping each other, because
they were fighting and brawling

00:43:19.820 --> 00:43:20.490 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:43:20.490 --> 00:43:22.880 align:middle line:84%
Because-- I don't
understand it, of course.

00:43:22.880 --> 00:43:24.680 align:middle line:90%
And I used to be a sportscaster.

00:43:24.680 --> 00:43:27.210 align:middle line:84%
But I don't understand the
mania and what's swept up

00:43:27.210 --> 00:43:30.660 align:middle line:84%
and what people are endowing
that sport with by way

00:43:30.660 --> 00:43:33.425 align:middle line:84%
of their emotions and their
commitment and their passion

00:43:33.425 --> 00:43:36.170 align:middle line:84%
into something
really so irrelevant.

00:43:36.170 --> 00:43:38.572 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: For them, it's--
I can't talk for all these

00:43:38.572 --> 00:43:40.530 align:middle line:84%
people, because everyone
has a different reason

00:43:40.530 --> 00:43:41.820 align:middle line:90%
for their connection to it.

00:43:41.820 --> 00:43:43.650 align:middle line:90%
It's a form of social identity.

00:43:43.650 --> 00:43:45.844 align:middle line:84%
It's a need for
attachment to something.

00:43:45.844 --> 00:43:48.010 align:middle line:84%
And if we can't attach with
something which gives us

00:43:48.010 --> 00:43:51.450 align:middle line:84%
fulfillment, then we
look for something.

00:43:51.450 --> 00:43:55.270 align:middle line:84%
And it's a very powerful
release mechanism.

00:43:55.270 --> 00:43:57.920 align:middle line:84%
Now, the working week
is another example.

00:43:57.920 --> 00:44:01.260 align:middle line:84%
Why do we-- most of us
have the weekend off.

00:44:01.260 --> 00:44:05.260 align:middle line:84%
Why are such drugs as
alcohol socially acceptable?

00:44:05.260 --> 00:44:07.130 align:middle line:84%
It's because we go
out on the weekend.

00:44:07.130 --> 00:44:08.995 align:middle line:90%
We have complete blow out.

00:44:08.995 --> 00:44:10.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Go to
your football match,

00:44:10.690 --> 00:44:14.400 align:middle line:84%
then have a blow out or
the two at the same time.

00:44:14.400 --> 00:44:17.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Come back to work
Monday morning feeling happy,

00:44:17.120 --> 00:44:18.440 align:middle line:90%
because you felt like you've--

00:44:18.440 --> 00:44:19.856 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You've
gotten to release

00:44:19.856 --> 00:44:21.530 align:middle line:84%
all of that anxiety,
stress, and so

00:44:21.530 --> 00:44:23.370 align:middle line:90%
forth for a short bit of time.

00:44:23.370 --> 00:44:25.210 align:middle line:84%
So with a generation
that's coming

00:44:25.210 --> 00:44:28.885 align:middle line:84%
in more connected and more
holistic in their thought,

00:44:28.885 --> 00:44:31.190 align:middle line:84%
this should-- we
should see a dying down

00:44:31.190 --> 00:44:32.920 align:middle line:84%
of this kind of
attachment as well?

00:44:32.920 --> 00:44:35.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Well, I feel
it'll be more organic,

00:44:35.390 --> 00:44:39.080 align:middle line:84%
because they'll-- the
new generation will look

00:44:39.080 --> 00:44:41.590 align:middle line:84%
in different areas
for nourishment.

00:44:41.590 --> 00:44:44.360 align:middle line:84%
And also, because
they're connecting

00:44:44.360 --> 00:44:48.740 align:middle line:84%
with an instinctual
intelligence, then they'll be--

00:44:48.740 --> 00:44:51.350 align:middle line:90%
they'll feel less of the lack.

00:44:51.350 --> 00:44:54.610 align:middle line:84%
Now, we need nourishment, but
how do we find nourishment?

00:44:54.610 --> 00:44:57.500 align:middle line:84%
Now, a lot of the
extremism is-- comes

00:44:57.500 --> 00:45:02.260 align:middle line:84%
from a lack of self worth,
which is also encouraged

00:45:02.260 --> 00:45:05.030 align:middle line:84%
by society to
increase dependency.

00:45:05.030 --> 00:45:07.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No wonder we're
trying to hide what we feel

00:45:07.310 --> 00:45:09.535 align:middle line:84%
or the shameful aspects
of self, really.

00:45:09.535 --> 00:45:10.690 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Transparency.

00:45:10.690 --> 00:45:11.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:45:11.590 --> 00:45:12.900 align:middle line:90%
We're afraid of transparency.

00:45:12.900 --> 00:45:14.960 align:middle line:84%
We're made to feel
ashamed of ourselves.

00:45:14.960 --> 00:45:16.840 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And if we
feel good in ourselves,

00:45:16.840 --> 00:45:18.580 align:middle line:90%
transparency isn't an issue.

00:45:18.580 --> 00:45:23.340 align:middle line:84%
Another word for transparency
is sharing, collaboration.

00:45:23.340 --> 00:45:26.940 align:middle line:84%
And we've been conditioned
not to collaborate.

00:45:26.940 --> 00:45:29.894 align:middle line:84%
An example is, when I was
at school and make yourself,

00:45:29.894 --> 00:45:31.810 align:middle line:84%
if we wanted to collaborate
with our neighbor,

00:45:31.810 --> 00:45:32.893 align:middle line:90%
you got your hand slapped.

00:45:32.893 --> 00:45:34.000 align:middle line:90%
It was called cheating.

00:45:34.000 --> 00:45:36.539 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exactly, except
in the Waldorf School.

00:45:36.539 --> 00:45:38.330 align:middle line:84%
I remember, the one
thing I loved about it.

00:45:38.330 --> 00:45:40.040 align:middle line:84%
My son was in the
Waldorf system.

00:45:40.040 --> 00:45:41.630 align:middle line:84%
And that was the
only system I notice

00:45:41.630 --> 00:45:44.140 align:middle line:84%
where they did this, where
the teacher would say,

00:45:44.140 --> 00:45:46.050 align:middle line:84%
please, you're going to
have a test tomorrow.

00:45:46.050 --> 00:45:47.090 align:middle line:90%
Share with each other.

00:45:47.090 --> 00:45:48.220 align:middle line:90%
I'm leaving the room.

00:45:48.220 --> 00:45:50.600 align:middle line:84%
And he encouraged them to
all share their information.

00:45:50.600 --> 00:45:53.150 align:middle line:84%
He said, it's best for
all of you if you do that.

00:45:53.150 --> 00:45:55.200 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, that's
the wave of the future.

00:45:55.200 --> 00:45:56.070 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Indeed.

00:45:56.070 --> 00:45:58.310 align:middle line:84%
And they were spot on
with that, and earlier.

00:45:58.310 --> 00:46:02.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes,
creating-- he was trying

00:46:02.380 --> 00:46:06.210 align:middle line:84%
to discourage the need for
competition within the group.

00:46:06.210 --> 00:46:08.040 align:middle line:84%
And now, so how does
competition factor

00:46:08.040 --> 00:46:09.585 align:middle line:90%
into this new generation?

00:46:09.585 --> 00:46:11.880 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Well, as
I've talked about,

00:46:11.880 --> 00:46:14.010 align:middle line:84%
we're moving toward
different value systems.

00:46:14.010 --> 00:46:17.580 align:middle line:84%
And so I call them C values,
because in English language,

00:46:17.580 --> 00:46:19.430 align:middle line:90%
these words are C words.

00:46:19.430 --> 00:46:23.490 align:middle line:84%
They're competition,
conflict, control.

00:46:23.490 --> 00:46:25.650 align:middle line:84%
And I say that the
new values which

00:46:25.650 --> 00:46:27.550 align:middle line:84%
will be taken on board
by the new generations

00:46:27.550 --> 00:46:31.250 align:middle line:84%
will be collaboration,
compassion, communication,

00:46:31.250 --> 00:46:32.980 align:middle line:90%
and consciousness.

00:46:32.980 --> 00:46:35.740 align:middle line:84%
And so competition,
it keeps us fighting

00:46:35.740 --> 00:46:38.350 align:middle line:84%
against the Joneses or
the people next door.

00:46:38.350 --> 00:46:41.700 align:middle line:84%
Because it wants--
we feel that we

00:46:41.700 --> 00:46:44.142 align:middle line:84%
want to get to the
top of the ladder.

00:46:44.142 --> 00:46:46.650 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're
expected of us.

00:46:46.650 --> 00:46:50.310 align:middle line:84%
And to get there, we have
to push everyone away.

00:46:50.310 --> 00:46:52.410 align:middle line:84%
And then that's the
control mechanism

00:46:52.410 --> 00:46:56.390 align:middle line:84%
which helps society to
continue to engineer itself

00:46:56.390 --> 00:46:59.780 align:middle line:84%
and to keep the top players
there and the masses

00:46:59.780 --> 00:47:01.260 align:middle line:90%
without access.

00:47:01.260 --> 00:47:04.170 align:middle line:84%
And that's another key
word, Regina, is access.

00:47:04.170 --> 00:47:08.970 align:middle line:84%
We're moving into the age of
access-- open source software,

00:47:08.970 --> 00:47:13.160 align:middle line:84%
access to information, access
to other minds and other hearts.

00:47:13.160 --> 00:47:15.496 align:middle line:84%
Now, that's another
exponential energy.

00:47:15.496 --> 00:47:18.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How does that
not become hijacked?

00:47:18.700 --> 00:47:21.330 align:middle line:84%
Just as the
spiritual and new age

00:47:21.330 --> 00:47:23.620 align:middle line:84%
movements of expanded
awareness and consciousness

00:47:23.620 --> 00:47:26.940 align:middle line:84%
were hijacked into even
something like 2012,

00:47:26.940 --> 00:47:29.660 align:middle line:84%
how is the emergence of
their new consciousness

00:47:29.660 --> 00:47:32.259 align:middle line:84%
not going to be hijacked
again and turned

00:47:32.259 --> 00:47:33.550 align:middle line:90%
into something it shouldn't be?

00:47:33.550 --> 00:47:35.700 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Well, I'm
not saying it won't.

00:47:35.700 --> 00:47:38.540 align:middle line:84%
I feel that there'll
be attempts to do that.

00:47:38.540 --> 00:47:42.910 align:middle line:84%
What's changing is our, or
humanity's, response to that

00:47:42.910 --> 00:47:44.720 align:middle line:90%
and recognition of it.

00:47:44.720 --> 00:47:47.940 align:middle line:84%
Now, before, we
were-- many of us

00:47:47.940 --> 00:47:50.680 align:middle line:84%
were saying, what is
the real information.

00:47:50.680 --> 00:47:56.152 align:middle line:84%
We don't have-- we may not
have a fully developed detector

00:47:56.152 --> 00:47:58.730 align:middle line:84%
in-built with us to be able
to distinguish what's true

00:47:58.730 --> 00:47:59.880 align:middle line:90%
and what is false.

00:47:59.880 --> 00:48:01.910 align:middle line:90%
And that was our work.

00:48:01.910 --> 00:48:04.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're going to
have an inherent software that

00:48:04.500 --> 00:48:05.175 align:middle line:90%
detects the difference.

00:48:05.175 --> 00:48:05.870 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: More so.

00:48:05.870 --> 00:48:06.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:48:06.150 --> 00:48:07.858 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Now, our
generation perhaps had

00:48:07.858 --> 00:48:10.320 align:middle line:84%
to do more work on
themselves, to be

00:48:10.320 --> 00:48:12.660 align:middle line:90%
able to have a feeling, a sense.

00:48:12.660 --> 00:48:17.150 align:middle line:84%
And so when there's an increased
instinctual intelligence,

00:48:17.150 --> 00:48:19.610 align:middle line:84%
as opposed to
acquired information,

00:48:19.610 --> 00:48:23.055 align:middle line:84%
then that recognition
will be more immediate.

00:48:23.055 --> 00:48:25.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you say
this is essentially

00:48:25.460 --> 00:48:29.670 align:middle line:84%
the rise of inner authority,
rather than external authority.

00:48:29.670 --> 00:48:33.270 align:middle line:84%
This will be-- we're the
bridging generation, or then

00:48:33.270 --> 00:48:35.790 align:middle line:84%
ones younger than us are
the bridging generation

00:48:35.790 --> 00:48:38.790 align:middle line:84%
to the move toward
inner authority, which

00:48:38.790 --> 00:48:39.950 align:middle line:90%
changes the whole game.

00:48:39.950 --> 00:48:43.910 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And this is a natural
endowment of the human being.

00:48:43.910 --> 00:48:49.170 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we've always had
it, but it's been stifled,

00:48:49.170 --> 00:48:54.240 align:middle line:84%
and it's been
basically denied us

00:48:54.240 --> 00:48:56.330 align:middle line:84%
through-- we talk
about conditioning

00:48:56.330 --> 00:48:58.280 align:middle line:90%
and the age of dependency.

00:48:58.280 --> 00:49:00.350 align:middle line:84%
And even now, we're
dependent on everything,

00:49:00.350 --> 00:49:03.460 align:middle line:84%
whether it's food
sourcing, security,

00:49:03.460 --> 00:49:07.450 align:middle line:84%
a roof over our head--
the basic needs of Maslow.

00:49:07.450 --> 00:49:10.700 align:middle line:84%
And as Abraham Maslow said, if
we can't cover our basic needs,

00:49:10.700 --> 00:49:13.450 align:middle line:84%
we cannot work toward
self-actualization.

00:49:13.450 --> 00:49:16.214 align:middle line:84%
To work on ourselves
is a luxury.

00:49:16.214 --> 00:49:17.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: For most
people, because we're

00:49:17.880 --> 00:49:19.230 align:middle line:90%
exhausted at the end of the day.

00:49:19.230 --> 00:49:19.935 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Of course, yeah.

00:49:19.935 --> 00:49:21.684 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, working
a couple jobs just

00:49:21.684 --> 00:49:23.070 align:middle line:90%
to keep roof over head.

00:49:23.070 --> 00:49:27.030 align:middle line:84%
So along with this comes the
emergence, or reemergence,

00:49:27.030 --> 00:49:31.260 align:middle line:84%
of respect and embracing
of the feminine aspect

00:49:31.260 --> 00:49:32.110 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:49:32.110 --> 00:49:36.900 align:middle line:84%
And you say that the internet
embraces the feminine.

00:49:36.900 --> 00:49:39.730 align:middle line:84%
It reflects feminine
aspect of consciousness.

00:49:39.730 --> 00:49:41.172 align:middle line:90%
How so?

00:49:41.172 --> 00:49:44.150 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Because
it's multi-relational.

00:49:44.150 --> 00:49:46.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, when I talk about
feminine consciousness,

00:49:46.440 --> 00:49:49.619 align:middle line:84%
again, we do suffer
from vocabulary.

00:49:49.619 --> 00:49:52.160 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not trying to create a
divide between male and female.

00:49:52.160 --> 00:49:53.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, no,
it's more yin-yang.

00:49:53.370 --> 00:49:54.010 align:middle line:90%
I get that.

00:49:54.010 --> 00:49:56.560 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: There are aspects
of each, which we will have,

00:49:56.560 --> 00:50:00.310 align:middle line:84%
but which maybe are
manifested more by others.

00:50:00.310 --> 00:50:05.610 align:middle line:84%
Now, the female consciousness
is one of, let's say,

00:50:05.610 --> 00:50:12.120 align:middle line:84%
multi-relational tasking, the
ability to connect, to share,

00:50:12.120 --> 00:50:13.420 align:middle line:90%
and collaborate.

00:50:13.420 --> 00:50:15.240 align:middle line:90%
And it's non-linear.

00:50:15.240 --> 00:50:19.910 align:middle line:84%
Now, a male consciousness may be
more goal orientated and fixed

00:50:19.910 --> 00:50:23.550 align:middle line:84%
on completing a task
rather than moving

00:50:23.550 --> 00:50:25.656 align:middle line:90%
through several processes.

00:50:25.656 --> 00:50:27.960 align:middle line:84%
Now, processional
consciousness may

00:50:27.960 --> 00:50:30.925 align:middle line:90%
be more of the feminine energy.

00:50:30.925 --> 00:50:33.030 align:middle line:84%
Now, the internet
works that way.

00:50:33.030 --> 00:50:37.360 align:middle line:84%
And we can say it's
quite circular.

00:50:37.360 --> 00:50:40.280 align:middle line:84%
Now, one example
which I've referred to

00:50:40.280 --> 00:50:44.040 align:middle line:84%
is that if we look in
history, an institution which

00:50:44.040 --> 00:50:47.160 align:middle line:84%
has a very strong male
consciousness manifestation

00:50:47.160 --> 00:50:49.990 align:middle line:90%
has been orthodox religion.

00:50:49.990 --> 00:50:53.870 align:middle line:84%
Now, we've had the priest at
the top, not allowing access

00:50:53.870 --> 00:50:57.467 align:middle line:90%
to any information, controlled.

00:50:57.467 --> 00:50:58.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Vertical access.

00:50:58.550 --> 00:51:00.370 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Vertical, yeah.

00:51:00.370 --> 00:51:02.450 align:middle line:90%
And now we had the Inquisition.

00:51:02.450 --> 00:51:04.020 align:middle line:90%
We had the witch hunts.

00:51:04.020 --> 00:51:08.660 align:middle line:84%
We had the-- many of the
female population stigmatized

00:51:08.660 --> 00:51:09.890 align:middle line:90%
for being witches.

00:51:09.890 --> 00:51:11.290 align:middle line:90%
And how did they gather?

00:51:11.290 --> 00:51:12.550 align:middle line:90%
They gathered in circles.

00:51:12.550 --> 00:51:15.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, you have this imagery
of the vertical controlled

00:51:15.860 --> 00:51:19.570 align:middle line:84%
and this feminine coming
together in circles, gathering.

00:51:19.570 --> 00:51:22.620 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing more than
putting the fear into authority

00:51:22.620 --> 00:51:23.970 align:middle line:90%
than people gathering.

00:51:23.970 --> 00:51:25.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:51:25.050 --> 00:51:28.670 align:middle line:84%
And you even call that
feminine yin energy

00:51:28.670 --> 00:51:30.830 align:middle line:84%
having a magical
presence to it, which

00:51:30.830 --> 00:51:32.810 align:middle line:84%
is what created the
repression of it

00:51:32.810 --> 00:51:35.350 align:middle line:84%
within these old patriarchal
systems to begin with.

00:51:35.350 --> 00:51:37.970 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: It's
something very sacred.

00:51:37.970 --> 00:51:39.925 align:middle line:84%
Gathering, sharing,
coming together

00:51:39.925 --> 00:51:41.450 align:middle line:90%
is something very sacred.

00:51:41.450 --> 00:51:46.060 align:middle line:84%
So when we have such things
as the Burning Man event,

00:51:46.060 --> 00:51:48.340 align:middle line:84%
or even now, the rise
of music festivals--

00:51:48.340 --> 00:51:51.610 align:middle line:84%
in England, Glastonbury
is the major example.

00:51:51.610 --> 00:51:53.630 align:middle line:84%
Now, we can say
it's very tribal,

00:51:53.630 --> 00:51:55.970 align:middle line:84%
but there's an energy
there which we share,

00:51:55.970 --> 00:51:59.400 align:middle line:84%
which is a collective
field energy, which

00:51:59.400 --> 00:52:01.270 align:middle line:90%
has always been there.

00:52:01.270 --> 00:52:03.910 align:middle line:84%
But people feel energy--
energized by that.

00:52:03.910 --> 00:52:07.004 align:middle line:84%
And many people feel
that's so natural.

00:52:07.004 --> 00:52:08.295 align:middle line:90%
That's our natural inheritance.

00:52:08.295 --> 00:52:09.770 align:middle line:90%
We feel inspired by it.

00:52:09.770 --> 00:52:11.860 align:middle line:90%
It's something very sacred.

00:52:11.860 --> 00:52:15.080 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we could
go as far as to say

00:52:15.080 --> 00:52:19.685 align:middle line:84%
that these gatherings are a
new shamanizing of humanity.

00:52:19.685 --> 00:52:21.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, yes.

00:52:21.450 --> 00:52:24.010 align:middle line:84%
And so that will be
more common expression

00:52:24.010 --> 00:52:27.170 align:middle line:84%
of the generation that's rising,
of course, the need to gather.

00:52:27.170 --> 00:52:30.330 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about,
from these young kids

00:52:30.330 --> 00:52:33.710 align:middle line:84%
and the ones just prior to
them, the emerging genius

00:52:33.710 --> 00:52:35.210 align:middle line:84%
that you talk
about in your book.

00:52:35.210 --> 00:52:39.280 align:middle line:84%
And we can even talk about--
use Steven Gonzales Jr.

00:52:39.280 --> 00:52:42.210 align:middle line:84%
as an example this kind
of shocking genius.

00:52:42.210 --> 00:52:43.940 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was
precocious at one time.

00:52:43.940 --> 00:52:46.148 align:middle line:84%
Now I see that this is just
the way it's going to be,

00:52:46.148 --> 00:52:47.082 align:middle line:90%
and it's lovely.

00:52:47.082 --> 00:52:49.040 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And we're seeing
instances popping up

00:52:49.040 --> 00:52:53.470 align:middle line:84%
with new YouTube videos all
around the net of young people

00:52:53.470 --> 00:52:56.389 align:middle line:84%
coming forward, giving
speeches at 12 years old.

00:52:56.389 --> 00:52:57.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Shockingly brilliant.

00:52:57.680 --> 00:53:01.360 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: 11 years old-- and
they understand the system.

00:53:01.360 --> 00:53:03.730 align:middle line:84%
They're saying, well,
what is going on?

00:53:03.730 --> 00:53:06.660 align:middle line:84%
Now, in the past, we may
have called them prodigies.

00:53:06.660 --> 00:53:10.190 align:middle line:84%
And perhaps many prodigies
were an earlier wave of this.

00:53:10.190 --> 00:53:12.770 align:middle line:84%
Now, I think we're going to
come a time where we may just

00:53:12.770 --> 00:53:15.630 align:middle line:84%
scrap the word genius because
there are too many of them.

00:53:15.630 --> 00:53:18.200 align:middle line:84%
You can't have a world
of geniuses all over.

00:53:18.200 --> 00:53:24.510 align:middle line:84%
So another phrase that I use is
that this is not the new age;

00:53:24.510 --> 00:53:25.390 align:middle line:90%
it's the new normal.

00:53:25.390 --> 00:53:26.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:53:26.040 --> 00:53:28.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And for
me, that's critical.

00:53:28.660 --> 00:53:30.700 align:middle line:84%
Is to normalize
what we're moving

00:53:30.700 --> 00:53:33.250 align:middle line:84%
into so the young
children don't feel

00:53:33.250 --> 00:53:35.120 align:middle line:84%
that they're something
really different.

00:53:35.120 --> 00:53:36.192 align:middle line:90%
They're not weird.

00:53:36.192 --> 00:53:37.400 align:middle line:90%
We shouldn't stigmatize them.

00:53:37.400 --> 00:53:39.160 align:middle line:90%
They are the new normal.

00:53:39.160 --> 00:53:41.915 align:middle line:84%
And the new normal are
these young children

00:53:41.915 --> 00:53:44.160 align:middle line:90%
who, for us, seem like geniuses.

00:53:44.160 --> 00:53:46.460 align:middle line:84%
For example, I talk
about in the book

00:53:46.460 --> 00:53:51.070 align:middle line:84%
young children writing
applications for programs

00:53:51.070 --> 00:53:56.010 align:middle line:84%
that help people to want
anti-illness, anti-bullying.

00:53:56.010 --> 00:53:57.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, yes.

00:53:57.430 --> 00:53:57.930 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:53:57.930 --> 00:53:58.950 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Go ahead.

00:53:58.950 --> 00:54:01.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, you go ahead,
more examples, please.

00:54:01.140 --> 00:54:03.790 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Well, the young
children who wrote an app

00:54:03.790 --> 00:54:06.020 align:middle line:84%
for young children at
school to connect with it,

00:54:06.020 --> 00:54:10.306 align:middle line:84%
to talk about their bullying
experiences and to gain help;

00:54:10.306 --> 00:54:13.360 align:middle line:84%
and a young boy-- I
forget his name now--

00:54:13.360 --> 00:54:16.020 align:middle line:84%
who suffered from
illness-- I think cancer--

00:54:16.020 --> 00:54:17.540 align:middle line:90%
wrote an app to actually--

00:54:17.540 --> 00:54:20.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, I think that
was Steven Gonzales, yes.

00:54:20.050 --> 00:54:24.300 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Now, their
age-- in one instance,

00:54:24.300 --> 00:54:26.960 align:middle line:84%
another young girl wrote an
app for a school project.

00:54:26.960 --> 00:54:29.560 align:middle line:84%
And the school didn't
believe or couldn't

00:54:29.560 --> 00:54:31.190 align:middle line:84%
believe that she
actually wrote it.

00:54:31.190 --> 00:54:36.670 align:middle line:84%
So they actually asked her to
write it again with monitors,

00:54:36.670 --> 00:54:38.730 align:middle line:84%
to see that she had the
capacity to write it.

00:54:38.730 --> 00:54:41.540 align:middle line:84%
We don't have that faith,
unless we can see it.

00:54:41.540 --> 00:54:43.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:54:43.520 --> 00:54:45.480 align:middle line:90%
I find that fascinating.

00:54:45.480 --> 00:54:48.670 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that,
if you go further into this,

00:54:48.670 --> 00:54:52.190 align:middle line:84%
and if you want to dive down to
this end of the pool-- and not

00:54:52.190 --> 00:54:53.684 align:middle line:90%
everybody's on board with this.

00:54:53.684 --> 00:54:55.600 align:middle line:84%
But the interesting thing
is, we look at that.

00:54:55.600 --> 00:54:57.520 align:middle line:84%
And then our
generation would almost

00:54:57.520 --> 00:55:03.100 align:middle line:84%
have an envy to be so free, to
be so brilliant and so open,

00:55:03.100 --> 00:55:06.290 align:middle line:84%
to be connected, passionate,
have the heart open once again.

00:55:06.290 --> 00:55:08.920 align:middle line:84%
From that, shouldn't
we see a huge shift

00:55:08.920 --> 00:55:11.950 align:middle line:84%
in creativity,
levels of creativity?

00:55:11.950 --> 00:55:12.670 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yes.

00:55:12.670 --> 00:55:14.740 align:middle line:84%
And also, a thing
to say, Regina,

00:55:14.740 --> 00:55:17.462 align:middle line:84%
is that it may not
be all smooth, easy.

00:55:17.462 --> 00:55:19.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I don't
think the transition is

00:55:19.420 --> 00:55:21.120 align:middle line:90%
going to be smooth at all.

00:55:21.120 --> 00:55:24.100 align:middle line:84%
Like you say, and as I
said earlier, in nature,

00:55:24.100 --> 00:55:25.510 align:middle line:90%
these things happen over time.

00:55:25.510 --> 00:55:28.280 align:middle line:84%
And there's always that
rough spot in the transition.

00:55:28.280 --> 00:55:31.010 align:middle line:84%
Let's just assume we're going
through some rough spots ahead.

00:55:31.010 --> 00:55:32.490 align:middle line:90%
But let's go beyond that.

00:55:32.490 --> 00:55:34.460 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: And those
sandpaper moments,

00:55:34.460 --> 00:55:37.950 align:middle line:84%
those rough spots are
the catalysts for change,

00:55:37.950 --> 00:55:39.740 align:middle line:90%
catalysts for creativity.

00:55:39.740 --> 00:55:41.230 align:middle line:90%
So we need them.

00:55:41.230 --> 00:55:42.860 align:middle line:90%
And creativity is infectious.

00:55:42.860 --> 00:55:45.790 align:middle line:84%
It's not only diseases
which are infectious.

00:55:45.790 --> 00:55:47.405 align:middle line:90%
Good things are infectious.

00:55:47.405 --> 00:55:49.660 align:middle line:84%
And I think creativity
is going to be

00:55:49.660 --> 00:55:53.510 align:middle line:84%
one of the new
infections that are

00:55:53.510 --> 00:55:55.400 align:middle line:84%
going to enter
the global sphere.

00:55:55.400 --> 00:55:59.500 align:middle line:84%
And so for example, if a
young child or even a parent

00:55:59.500 --> 00:56:01.450 align:middle line:84%
looks at these
examples on YouTube

00:56:01.450 --> 00:56:03.270 align:middle line:84%
of another young
child doing this,

00:56:03.270 --> 00:56:05.650 align:middle line:84%
then the parent will say,
well, maybe to their child--

00:56:05.650 --> 00:56:07.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, it's
possible, obviously.

00:56:07.430 --> 00:56:09.020 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: What do
you want to do?

00:56:09.020 --> 00:56:10.450 align:middle line:90%
How can I help you?

00:56:10.450 --> 00:56:13.400 align:middle line:84%
And the young child will
say, I may need this.

00:56:13.400 --> 00:56:14.300 align:middle line:90%
I may need that.

00:56:14.300 --> 00:56:17.690 align:middle line:84%
And the parent will say,
well, I'll help you, if I can.

00:56:17.690 --> 00:56:20.600 align:middle line:84%
So in the past, maybe the
parent would say to the child,

00:56:20.600 --> 00:56:23.250 align:middle line:84%
do you want to play
a musical instrument?

00:56:23.250 --> 00:56:26.400 align:middle line:84%
And that was the kind of one
of the aspects of creativity,

00:56:26.400 --> 00:56:28.230 align:middle line:90%
playing a musical instrument.

00:56:28.230 --> 00:56:30.070 align:middle line:84%
But that's going to
be a whole playing

00:56:30.070 --> 00:56:31.130 align:middle line:90%
field of new creativity.

00:56:31.130 --> 00:56:32.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is
going to create a need

00:56:32.330 --> 00:56:34.510 align:middle line:84%
for a completely different
way of education.

00:56:34.510 --> 00:56:36.160 align:middle line:84%
Can you talk about
your vision of that?

00:56:36.160 --> 00:56:36.743 align:middle line:90%
>>DENNIS: Yes.

00:56:36.743 --> 00:56:39.690 align:middle line:84%
Well, education
is going to be one

00:56:39.690 --> 00:56:42.100 align:middle line:84%
of the areas of
significant change.

00:56:42.100 --> 00:56:44.850 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to
be a game changer.

00:56:44.850 --> 00:56:48.310 align:middle line:84%
And we're seeing that
now with, for example,

00:56:48.310 --> 00:56:50.920 align:middle line:84%
such institutions as Khan
Academy on the internet,

00:56:50.920 --> 00:56:56.110 align:middle line:84%
where information is being
made available for anyone

00:56:56.110 --> 00:56:58.750 align:middle line:84%
to come into contact
with it and to use that.

00:56:58.750 --> 00:57:00.280 align:middle line:84%
It's a peer to
peer educational--

00:57:00.280 --> 00:57:01.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You think
the school room

00:57:01.550 --> 00:57:02.580 align:middle line:84%
is going to be a
thing of the past?

00:57:02.580 --> 00:57:03.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: Yeah, I
mean, the classroom.

00:57:03.540 --> 00:57:04.373 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Has to be.

00:57:04.373 --> 00:57:10.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DENNIS: The four
walls is a prison.

00:57:10.500 --> 00:57:14.570 align:middle line:84%
And the school
curriculum is a prison,

00:57:14.570 --> 00:57:18.540 align:middle line:84%
because that ideal of
learning in isolation,

00:57:18.540 --> 00:57:20.530 align:middle line:84%
but not-- I don't think
it's called learning.

00:57:20.530 --> 00:57:23.510 align:middle line:84%
I think it's called
memorization.

00:57:23.510 --> 00:57:28.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's a consequence of the
Industrial Revolution, the work

00:57:28.140 --> 00:57:31.550 align:middle line:84%
houses, were just to educate
the young children enough

00:57:31.550 --> 00:57:33.560 align:middle line:90%
to put them in the workforce.

00:57:33.560 --> 00:57:35.920 align:middle line:84%
